1
00:01:04,152 --> 00:01:06,988
QUEEN OF TEARS

2
00:01:07,697 --> 00:01:08,990
FINAL EPISODE

3
00:01:43,817 --> 00:01:44,859
Hae-in?

4
00:02:18,393 --> 00:02:19,811
Please come out, sir.

5
00:02:21,521 --> 00:02:22,814
Come out.

6
00:02:37,370 --> 00:02:39,038
It's a male, 35. TA patient.

7
00:02:39,122 --> 00:02:40,498
He's unconscious.

8
00:02:40,582 --> 00:02:42,667
-Move aside. -Coming through.

9
00:02:45,170 --> 00:02:47,005
Will you marry me?

10
00:02:50,508 --> 00:02:52,886
If we do get married,

11
00:02:54,345 --> 00:02:56,514
you might be quite surprised by who I am.

12
00:02:57,182 --> 00:02:59,267
You probably don't know this,

13
00:02:59,350 --> 00:03:01,728
but my family is different from yours.

14
00:03:01,811 --> 00:03:03,813
They couldn't be that different.

15
00:03:03,897 --> 00:03:05,106
You're wrong.

16
00:03:05,190 --> 00:03:08,693
You just don't know, but my family is very different.

17
00:03:08,776 --> 00:03:11,946
So you might become flustered and struggle to get along with them.

18
00:03:12,030 --> 00:03:14,073
Even if you put up with everything and feel lonely,

19
00:03:15,116 --> 00:03:16,492
I won't be able to side with you.

20
00:03:18,870 --> 00:03:21,039
Are you rejecting

21
00:03:21,122 --> 00:03:22,665
my proposal?

22
00:03:22,749 --> 00:03:24,042
No.

23
00:03:24,125 --> 00:03:27,045
I would've made it short if I did.

24
00:03:27,128 --> 00:03:28,504
That's all that matters.

25
00:03:29,797 --> 00:03:32,091
This isn't a simple matter.

26
00:03:32,175 --> 00:03:33,468
But I'm okay.

27
00:03:40,808 --> 00:03:42,393
If you're really okay…

28
00:03:46,356 --> 00:03:47,899
I want to marry you.

29
00:03:49,317 --> 00:03:51,903
I want to live with you.

30
00:04:00,745 --> 00:04:01,579
What are his vitals?

31
00:04:01,663 --> 00:04:03,081
His BP is 101 over 66.

32
00:04:03,164 --> 00:04:04,165
His oxygen is 92%…

33
00:04:04,249 --> 00:04:06,209
Let's say we get married.

34
00:04:06,292 --> 00:04:07,835
Even if you don't side with me,

35
00:04:08,503 --> 00:04:10,421
I can side with you, right?

36
00:04:11,506 --> 00:04:13,675
Then we'll be on the same team anyway.

37
00:04:14,550 --> 00:04:15,843
That's what marriage is.

38
00:04:16,469 --> 00:04:19,180
Being on the same side and in the same boat.

39
00:04:19,264 --> 00:04:23,101
And… if the boat capsizes, then we go down together.

40
00:04:23,184 --> 00:04:25,937
If you live, then I live too.

41
00:04:28,147 --> 00:04:29,065
That's what it is.

42
00:04:31,359 --> 00:04:32,193
Is that so?

43
00:04:35,863 --> 00:04:38,366
You might not know this,

44
00:04:38,449 --> 00:04:41,953
but life isn't easy.

45
00:04:42,036 --> 00:04:44,163
I was a victim of a real estate scam.

46
00:04:44,247 --> 00:04:45,331
But you're an attorney.

47
00:04:45,415 --> 00:04:46,624
I know, right?

48
00:04:49,294 --> 00:04:50,128
You see,

49
00:04:50,670 --> 00:04:52,505
professional scammers

50
00:04:53,298 --> 00:04:56,217
are smarter than attorneys.

51
00:04:57,593 --> 00:04:58,928
I was totally duped.

52
00:05:01,472 --> 00:05:03,599
But in the future,

53
00:05:03,683 --> 00:05:05,518
there will be many times

54
00:05:05,601 --> 00:05:07,645
when I'm even more flabbergasted,

55
00:05:07,729 --> 00:05:09,188
wronged,

56
00:05:09,272 --> 00:05:10,398
and upset.

57
00:05:11,107 --> 00:05:13,651
But I'd be very delighted

58
00:05:14,610 --> 00:05:17,697
if you were in the boat I was in.

59
00:05:19,073 --> 00:05:20,491
Even if we need to bail water out

60
00:05:21,367 --> 00:05:24,120
and row all night long, I'd have someone

61
00:05:25,830 --> 00:05:26,914
to rely on.

62
00:05:28,583 --> 00:05:29,834
Shouldn't we marry someone

63
00:05:29,917 --> 00:05:31,961
who makes us feel that way?

64
00:05:32,587 --> 00:05:33,463
That's why

65
00:05:34,130 --> 00:05:35,131
I'm…

66
00:05:38,009 --> 00:05:40,386
proposing to you today.

67
00:06:16,881 --> 00:06:18,049
Where is he?

68
00:06:19,342 --> 00:06:21,677
Here?

69
00:06:21,761 --> 00:06:23,304
Where?

70
00:06:25,598 --> 00:06:28,393
Excuse me. My son…

71
00:06:28,476 --> 00:06:29,310
He's here…

72
00:06:29,394 --> 00:06:30,436
Baek Hyun-woo.

73
00:06:31,062 --> 00:06:32,230
Doctor.

74
00:06:32,313 --> 00:06:34,649
We're looking for Baek Hyun-woo.

75
00:06:34,732 --> 00:06:36,150
Yes, he was…

76
00:06:36,234 --> 00:06:37,402
-What was it? -A car accident.

77
00:06:37,485 --> 00:06:38,986
-Yes, a car accident. -Mr. Baek?

78
00:06:39,070 --> 00:06:39,987
Is he alive?

79
00:06:40,071 --> 00:06:41,197
Yes.

80
00:06:41,280 --> 00:06:43,116
His ribs and liver were severely injured.

81
00:06:43,199 --> 00:06:45,910
There may be internal bleeding so we need to follow-up.

82
00:06:45,993 --> 00:06:47,120
Thank God.

83
00:06:47,203 --> 00:06:48,121
He's alive.

84
00:06:48,621 --> 00:06:49,580
Everything is fine.

85
00:06:50,164 --> 00:06:51,040
Honey.

86
00:06:51,707 --> 00:06:52,792
Doctor.

87
00:06:52,875 --> 00:06:54,794
Where is he right now?

88
00:06:54,877 --> 00:06:56,003
He's over there.

89
00:06:58,047 --> 00:06:59,757
-Hyun-woo. -He's been admitted.

90
00:07:05,138 --> 00:07:06,764
BAEK HYUN-WOO

91
00:08:10,661 --> 00:08:11,746
Are you up already?

92
00:08:12,371 --> 00:08:13,247
What is going on?

93
00:08:26,511 --> 00:08:27,553
Did you do it?

94
00:08:34,685 --> 00:08:36,145
Did you bring me here

95
00:08:37,063 --> 00:08:38,940
against my will?

96
00:08:39,023 --> 00:08:43,110
I told you I'd do anything to protect you.

97
00:08:43,194 --> 00:08:44,862
That's why you did this?

98
00:08:45,696 --> 00:08:49,158
Yes, I refuse to see you get duped and hurt by Hyun-woo again.

99
00:08:50,117 --> 00:08:50,993
That's why

100
00:08:52,870 --> 00:08:54,455
I had to use force.

101
00:08:56,249 --> 00:08:57,542
Where are we?

102
00:09:00,086 --> 00:09:01,003
Answer me first.

103
00:09:02,463 --> 00:09:04,215
Why did you go there to see him?

104
00:09:09,595 --> 00:09:11,013
You can't answer me.

105
00:09:18,604 --> 00:09:20,523
How long must I be understanding,

106
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:22,733
patient,

107
00:09:22,817 --> 00:09:23,985
and forgiving?

108
00:09:27,446 --> 00:09:29,031
I don't want to resent you.

109
00:09:30,825 --> 00:09:32,952
Actually, I saw the notebook.

110
00:09:34,662 --> 00:09:37,915
Someone had sent it from Germany. I must've written it before the surgery.

111
00:09:37,999 --> 00:09:40,376
It looked like my handwriting. But the details differed

112
00:09:40,459 --> 00:09:42,003
from what you had told me,

113
00:09:42,086 --> 00:09:43,296
so I wanted to check.

114
00:09:43,379 --> 00:09:45,464
That's why I wanted to confront him.

115
00:09:46,340 --> 00:09:47,174
Is that so?

116
00:09:49,051 --> 00:09:50,261
But to be honest,

117
00:09:50,344 --> 00:09:52,722
anyone could've copied my handwriting.

118
00:09:53,264 --> 00:09:55,057
There's no proof that it was me.

119
00:09:56,142 --> 00:09:58,060
It could've been all made up.

120
00:09:58,144 --> 00:09:59,395
So?

121
00:10:01,647 --> 00:10:03,065
You were right.

122
00:10:03,149 --> 00:10:05,276
I was thoughtless. I should've asked you first.

123
00:10:11,073 --> 00:10:14,827
I'm sorry that I suspected and upset you. It won't happen again.

124
00:10:15,536 --> 00:10:16,704
So…

125
00:10:16,787 --> 00:10:17,788
let's…

126
00:10:19,415 --> 00:10:20,416
Let's go home.

127
00:10:24,962 --> 00:10:26,380
If I was right

128
00:10:27,298 --> 00:10:29,634
and you were thoughtless, then listen to me.

129
00:10:30,801 --> 00:10:33,012
Let's leave together and…

130
00:10:34,180 --> 00:10:35,348
get married.

131
00:10:35,431 --> 00:10:37,433
A helicopter will come at dawn.

132
00:10:37,516 --> 00:10:39,477
I have everything planned out.

133
00:10:39,560 --> 00:10:40,561
You just need

134
00:10:41,437 --> 00:10:42,438
to follow me.

135
00:10:50,529 --> 00:10:53,282
What about the department store? I just got reinstated.

136
00:10:54,784 --> 00:10:57,495
A professional manager can take care of it

137
00:10:58,120 --> 00:10:59,205
until you return.

138
00:11:02,166 --> 00:11:03,000
Is that okay?

139
00:11:12,551 --> 00:11:13,386
Answer me.

140
00:11:18,557 --> 00:11:19,642
Okay, let's do that.

141
00:11:26,691 --> 00:11:29,151
Due to the snow and the unregistered license plate,

142
00:11:29,235 --> 00:11:31,070
I don't think I can track him anymore.

143
00:11:31,153 --> 00:11:32,446
Not even the police could.

144
00:11:36,075 --> 00:11:37,660
-Did you find her? -Why are you here?

145
00:11:37,743 --> 00:11:39,453
-Weren't you in the ER? -Answer me!

146
00:11:39,537 --> 00:11:40,663
You're a lunatic.

147
00:11:40,746 --> 00:11:42,748
Go back to the hospital.

148
00:11:42,832 --> 00:11:43,708
Okay?

149
00:11:45,626 --> 00:11:47,795
Why did you come here late at night?

150
00:11:53,926 --> 00:11:54,885
You see…

151
00:11:55,511 --> 00:11:57,596
Hyun-woo just called me.

152
00:11:57,680 --> 00:11:58,764
Hae-in disappeared.

153
00:11:58,848 --> 00:12:02,435
-Disappeared? -She just vanished into thin air.

154
00:12:02,518 --> 00:12:06,313
He told me not to tell you and to look into it discreetly.

155
00:12:06,397 --> 00:12:07,732
But I thought you should know.

156
00:12:07,815 --> 00:12:08,941
Tell Ms. Moh

157
00:12:09,024 --> 00:12:10,317
that Hae-in is missing.

158
00:12:11,652 --> 00:12:13,487
It'll be faster for her to find her.

159
00:12:16,615 --> 00:12:20,077
I think Mr. Yoon had something to do with it.

160
00:12:20,161 --> 00:12:22,163
Your inauguration is around the corner.

161
00:12:22,246 --> 00:12:25,249
I'm worried that this might cause problems.

162
00:12:26,083 --> 00:12:27,334
Okay. You may go.

163
00:12:28,711 --> 00:12:29,545
Yes, ma'am.

164
00:12:36,594 --> 00:12:38,345
I have evidence.

165
00:12:38,429 --> 00:12:42,057
So touch Hae-in one more time,

166
00:12:42,141 --> 00:12:46,103
and I will put you behind bars like I did with Hyun-woo.

167
00:12:51,650 --> 00:12:52,777
Hello.

168
00:12:54,487 --> 00:12:56,447
I'd like to move the money I have

169
00:12:57,031 --> 00:12:58,032
in the safe.

170
00:12:58,115 --> 00:13:01,410
Mr. Yoon converted it all into dollars and took it.

171
00:13:13,088 --> 00:13:14,340
She's leaving now.

172
00:13:36,237 --> 00:13:38,948
Mr. Pyeon's killer finally had a change of heart.

173
00:13:39,031 --> 00:13:41,742
He didn't specifically name Eun-sung,

174
00:13:41,826 --> 00:13:43,327
but he did mention an accomplice.

175
00:13:43,410 --> 00:13:44,870
I bet Eun-sung heard.

176
00:13:44,954 --> 00:13:47,790
He's probably planning to leave the country, right?

177
00:13:51,043 --> 00:13:51,877
Hey.

178
00:13:54,129 --> 00:13:55,256
Are you sleeping?

179
00:13:59,718 --> 00:14:00,553
Hyun-woo.

180
00:14:06,308 --> 00:14:07,142
Hyun-woo!

181
00:14:07,768 --> 00:14:08,686
Hey.

182
00:14:11,397 --> 00:14:12,273
I'm not sleeping.

183
00:14:14,859 --> 00:14:18,654
Then you should've said so or at least snored if you were sleeping!

184
00:14:18,737 --> 00:14:21,991
You just ran away from the ER. Imagine how terrified I was.

185
00:14:22,074 --> 00:14:24,076
I'm not going to die. Don't worry.

186
00:14:24,159 --> 00:14:25,661
This is driving me nuts.

187
00:14:28,247 --> 00:14:29,540
Hey, I'm a divorce attorney.

188
00:14:29,623 --> 00:14:30,958
I know.

189
00:14:31,041 --> 00:14:33,961
Divorce isn't favorable, but all my clients say

190
00:14:34,044 --> 00:14:37,423
that they're divorcing to have a happier future.

191
00:14:37,506 --> 00:14:40,217
In short, I have great pride in helping those

192
00:14:40,301 --> 00:14:41,969
who want to live better lives.

193
00:14:42,553 --> 00:14:43,888
-So? -But you're different.

194
00:14:43,971 --> 00:14:45,639
You don't care about yourself.

195
00:14:47,016 --> 00:14:48,642
You're digging your own grave.

196
00:14:50,603 --> 00:14:52,104
-Yang-gi-- -Just be yourself.

197
00:14:52,688 --> 00:14:54,857
Don't talk in a low, affectionate voice.

198
00:14:58,068 --> 00:15:00,821
Thank you for always being by my side.

199
00:15:04,116 --> 00:15:05,951
Don't act so differently.

200
00:15:07,286 --> 00:15:08,329
You're a good friend.

201
00:15:08,412 --> 00:15:10,247
Don't compliment me!

202
00:15:11,206 --> 00:15:12,833
Are you really dying or what?

203
00:15:28,557 --> 00:15:29,600
Where are we?

204
00:15:29,683 --> 00:15:30,893
It's our hunting ground.

205
00:15:31,769 --> 00:15:33,938
-Our villa is here. -Should I call the police?

206
00:15:34,021 --> 00:15:36,482
I'll call you after I go in and check.

207
00:15:36,565 --> 00:15:37,650
Call them then.

208
00:15:38,317 --> 00:15:39,276
Hey.

209
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:41,403
You're going by yourself? Hey!

210
00:16:01,966 --> 00:16:02,883
RESTRICTED AREA

211
00:16:34,289 --> 00:16:37,084
Down that way is a side door to the kitchen.

212
00:16:37,167 --> 00:16:38,544
We'd transport ingredients

213
00:16:38,627 --> 00:16:40,879
through that door when the chairman visited.

214
00:16:41,672 --> 00:16:42,548
Thank you.

215
00:16:42,631 --> 00:16:44,675
By the way, is something going on?

216
00:16:44,758 --> 00:16:48,679
Vehicles have been coming by and transporting things.

217
00:16:48,762 --> 00:16:49,638
I see.

218
00:16:51,181 --> 00:16:52,891
Don't worry about it.

219
00:16:54,059 --> 00:16:56,603
I'll explain everything once the dust settles.

220
00:17:03,027 --> 00:17:03,902
Why are you here?

221
00:17:06,947 --> 00:17:08,824
Where's my money? Is it here?

222
00:17:09,575 --> 00:17:10,492
I thought

223
00:17:11,577 --> 00:17:13,370
you came to say goodbye

224
00:17:13,454 --> 00:17:14,788
since I'll be leaving.

225
00:17:16,957 --> 00:17:20,836
You can leave if you want, but give me my money and the file.

226
00:17:22,046 --> 00:17:23,088
What file?

227
00:17:26,133 --> 00:17:26,967
I see.

228
00:17:29,470 --> 00:17:31,722
The proof that you killed the chairman?

229
00:17:31,805 --> 00:17:34,600
Were you really worried that I'd expose you?

230
00:17:36,810 --> 00:17:38,145
You know me.

231
00:17:40,397 --> 00:17:42,816
I was always good at keeping secrets.

232
00:17:55,621 --> 00:17:56,997
Thank you.

233
00:18:41,166 --> 00:18:42,543
I left something behind.

234
00:18:42,626 --> 00:18:43,710
You go ahead.

235
00:18:44,711 --> 00:18:45,546
All right.

236
00:18:58,433 --> 00:18:59,685
Why are you here?

237
00:19:00,811 --> 00:19:02,938
-To see you. -What if someone sees you?

238
00:19:03,689 --> 00:19:05,732
I'll be there soon. Be patient.

239
00:19:08,694 --> 00:19:09,987
Take a taxi back.

240
00:19:11,738 --> 00:19:12,948
Mom.

241
00:19:14,700 --> 00:19:15,909
Don't get caught.

242
00:19:20,873 --> 00:19:21,999
Su-wan!

243
00:19:22,082 --> 00:19:23,208
-Su-wan! -Su-wan!

244
00:19:23,292 --> 00:19:24,251
Su-wan!

245
00:19:24,334 --> 00:19:25,294
Oh, no!

246
00:19:25,377 --> 00:19:30,966
Su-wan!

247
00:19:31,550 --> 00:19:32,384
-Su-wan! -Su-wan!

248
00:19:38,807 --> 00:19:40,976
-What's going on? -There's been an accident!

249
00:19:41,059 --> 00:19:41,894
Oh, no!

250
00:19:41,977 --> 00:19:43,020
Where are the kids?

251
00:19:43,103 --> 00:19:44,271
Please wait.

252
00:19:44,771 --> 00:19:46,732
Please hurry and save them!

253
00:20:06,752 --> 00:20:07,753
Don't go there.

254
00:20:07,836 --> 00:20:10,297
-What's going on? -What's happening?

255
00:20:10,380 --> 00:20:12,883
-What's happening? -What's going on?

256
00:20:17,471 --> 00:20:18,597
Why haven't you left?

257
00:20:21,099 --> 00:20:22,017
Is he dead?

258
00:20:25,687 --> 00:20:27,439
You broke the boat.

259
00:20:27,522 --> 00:20:28,815
I saw it.

260
00:20:28,899 --> 00:20:29,775
But Mom.

261
00:20:29,858 --> 00:20:32,236
We can only live together if they die.

262
00:20:32,319 --> 00:20:34,613
That's why I didn't tell anyone.

263
00:20:37,199 --> 00:20:38,283
I thought doing that

264
00:20:38,367 --> 00:20:40,285
would mean you'd come to me soon.

265
00:20:40,911 --> 00:20:41,870
So I waited.

266
00:20:42,496 --> 00:20:43,914
You probably don't know

267
00:20:43,997 --> 00:20:46,416
how agonizing it is to wait for someone who'll never come.

268
00:20:46,500 --> 00:20:48,001
You're right. I don't.

269
00:20:48,085 --> 00:20:50,712
If Hae-in had also died back then,

270
00:20:50,796 --> 00:20:54,424
you wouldn't have disrupted my plan in this manner.

271
00:20:55,050 --> 00:20:56,301
That's my only regret.

272
00:21:00,347 --> 00:21:01,765
So where's the file?

273
00:21:05,352 --> 00:21:06,561
It's in my drawer.

274
00:21:07,688 --> 00:21:09,856
-The passcode is your birthday. -And the money?

275
00:21:10,357 --> 00:21:11,191
Why?

276
00:21:12,442 --> 00:21:14,569
You said to protect myself with that money.

277
00:21:15,153 --> 00:21:17,322
You said that was your way of loving me!

278
00:21:22,411 --> 00:21:23,245
Wait.

279
00:21:49,479 --> 00:21:50,314
Hae-in.

280
00:21:50,814 --> 00:21:51,940
Hae-in!

281
00:21:52,816 --> 00:21:54,735
Hae-in. Where is she?

282
00:22:42,657 --> 00:22:43,700
What's wrong?

283
00:22:46,661 --> 00:22:48,538
What's with your face? Did you get hurt?

284
00:22:49,623 --> 00:22:50,749
I'm okay.

285
00:22:50,832 --> 00:22:52,000
You don't look okay.

286
00:22:52,793 --> 00:22:54,795
Lean onto me, okay?

287
00:22:55,587 --> 00:22:56,797
It's okay.

288
00:22:56,880 --> 00:22:59,841
Go straight to reach the main gate.

289
00:22:59,925 --> 00:23:01,259
My friend is waiting there.

290
00:23:01,343 --> 00:23:02,594
Go first. I'll be there soon.

291
00:23:02,677 --> 00:23:04,262
What do you take me for?

292
00:23:04,346 --> 00:23:07,808
Was I the selfish type who'd leave my rescuer behind?

293
00:23:08,934 --> 00:23:09,768
That's not what--

294
00:23:09,851 --> 00:23:11,436
And I know everything.

295
00:23:12,229 --> 00:23:14,398
I know what you meant to me.

296
00:23:15,440 --> 00:23:17,692
I regret suspecting you.

297
00:23:17,776 --> 00:23:19,444
I'll apologize properly later.

298
00:23:23,657 --> 00:23:24,574
Just grab onto me.

299
00:23:27,035 --> 00:23:28,703
We're in the same boat tonight.

300
00:23:29,996 --> 00:23:31,415
We'll be moving together.

301
00:24:42,611 --> 00:24:44,279
Over here!

302
00:25:16,645 --> 00:25:18,063
Why are you with him?

303
00:25:20,815 --> 00:25:21,900
Come to me.

304
00:25:21,983 --> 00:25:23,109
If you do,

305
00:25:23,985 --> 00:25:26,071
I'll turn a blind eye to everything.

306
00:25:26,738 --> 00:25:28,657
We agreed to leave together!

307
00:25:28,740 --> 00:25:30,116
I'm sorry,

308
00:25:30,825 --> 00:25:32,452
but that won't happen.

309
00:25:32,953 --> 00:25:35,914
I felt uneasy and disliked you even when I couldn't remember anything.

310
00:25:36,623 --> 00:25:38,124
And now, I know why.

311
00:25:40,669 --> 00:25:42,337
Why do I make you feel uneasy?

312
00:25:44,047 --> 00:25:45,674
Tell me. Why don't you like me?

313
00:25:46,550 --> 00:25:50,220
My life was ruined because of you, yet I still tried my best! So why?

314
00:25:50,303 --> 00:25:52,222
Eun-sung! That's enough!

315
00:25:52,305 --> 00:25:54,641
-It's all over now! -Shut up! It's not over!

316
00:26:02,649 --> 00:26:03,483
It's okay.

317
00:26:04,776 --> 00:26:06,319
It's not too late, Hae-in.

318
00:26:06,403 --> 00:26:07,737
Let's go. Okay?

319
00:26:07,821 --> 00:26:09,781
Snap out of it!

320
00:26:09,864 --> 00:26:11,241
I won't go. Over my dead body.

321
00:26:15,245 --> 00:26:16,371
Really?

322
00:26:21,459 --> 00:26:22,669
Over your dead body?

323
00:26:36,683 --> 00:26:37,684
Really?

324
00:26:38,101 --> 00:26:40,687
-Eun-sung! -Drop the rifle right now!

325
00:26:40,770 --> 00:26:42,272
We'll fire if you don't!

326
00:26:45,025 --> 00:26:46,401
I'm sorry, Hae-in.

327
00:26:53,825 --> 00:26:55,285
But I can't leave you here.

328
00:26:56,286 --> 00:26:57,120
I'm going…

329
00:26:59,372 --> 00:27:02,125
to take you with me even if I have to kill you.

330
00:28:03,061 --> 00:28:03,895
No…

331
00:28:05,021 --> 00:28:05,897
Mr. Baek.

332
00:28:07,649 --> 00:28:08,942
Mr. Baek.

333
00:28:09,567 --> 00:28:11,653
Mr. Baek, open your eyes. Please?

334
00:28:14,197 --> 00:28:15,740
Mr. Baek, no!

335
00:28:15,824 --> 00:28:18,201
Please wake up! Please?

336
00:28:18,284 --> 00:28:19,994
Help us!

337
00:28:25,333 --> 00:28:26,167
Hyun-woo!

338
00:28:27,794 --> 00:28:29,045
Baek Hyun-woo!

339
00:28:52,360 --> 00:28:54,487
We'll take him to a major trauma center.

340
00:28:54,571 --> 00:28:55,905
Tell them a man was shot

341
00:28:55,989 --> 00:28:58,450
-and needs urgent surgery immediately. -Yes, sir.

342
00:29:08,334 --> 00:29:09,544
His bleeding won't stop.

343
00:29:09,627 --> 00:29:10,920
Inform the hospital!

344
00:29:11,004 --> 00:29:13,047
His BP is 80 over 50. It's dropping!

345
00:29:13,131 --> 00:29:15,133
Sir, I'll press down on your wound.

346
00:29:19,053 --> 00:29:19,888
Mr. Baek.

347
00:29:21,514 --> 00:29:22,557
Open your eyes.

348
00:29:24,476 --> 00:29:25,310
Okay?

349
00:29:25,810 --> 00:29:28,313
We're taking you to a hospital. You'll be okay.

350
00:29:29,397 --> 00:29:30,315
Hang in there.

351
00:29:32,400 --> 00:29:33,401
I'm…

352
00:29:39,157 --> 00:29:39,991
okay.

353
00:29:55,632 --> 00:29:56,633
Don't cry.

354
00:30:47,642 --> 00:30:49,477
Don't go anywhere.

355
00:30:49,561 --> 00:30:50,979
I'm not going anywhere.

356
00:30:51,062 --> 00:30:51,896
I'll be waiting.

357
00:30:52,605 --> 00:30:54,065
Don't worry about me.

358
00:30:55,191 --> 00:30:56,609
See you after the surgery.

359
00:31:14,043 --> 00:31:15,587
You won't go anywhere, right?

360
00:31:17,171 --> 00:31:20,633
What if I don't remember anything or recognize you?

361
00:31:21,843 --> 00:31:23,261
What if I mistreat you?

362
00:31:23,344 --> 00:31:25,638
It won't be my first rodeo.

363
00:31:25,722 --> 00:31:27,515
That won't matter at all.

364
00:31:27,599 --> 00:31:29,475
Just get the surgery

365
00:31:30,768 --> 00:31:31,769
and come back.

366
00:31:33,229 --> 00:31:35,398
Make sure you come back.

367
00:31:36,274 --> 00:31:37,442
I'll be back.

368
00:31:37,525 --> 00:31:41,029
Please take care of me when I return.

369
00:31:45,742 --> 00:31:47,201
That's exactly what I did.

370
00:31:48,745 --> 00:31:50,455
I forgot who he was.

371
00:31:51,956 --> 00:31:53,458
I treated him like a stranger.

372
00:31:54,792 --> 00:31:55,793
I mistreated him…

373
00:31:57,921 --> 00:31:59,714
so much.

374
00:33:23,631 --> 00:33:24,716
Did something happen?

375
00:33:24,799 --> 00:33:26,009
I heard a ruckus.

376
00:33:26,092 --> 00:33:28,219
-Do you know Mr. Yoon Eun-sung? -Yes. Why?

377
00:33:28,302 --> 00:33:29,846
He just passed away.

378
00:33:51,492 --> 00:33:52,785
When will you return?

379
00:33:59,834 --> 00:34:00,918
Mom!

380
00:34:01,627 --> 00:34:02,879
Mom!

381
00:34:02,962 --> 00:34:05,339
Come back soon!

382
00:34:05,882 --> 00:34:07,925
I'll be waiting for you!

383
00:34:08,009 --> 00:34:09,010
Mom!

384
00:34:10,261 --> 00:34:11,512
Mom!

385
00:34:13,556 --> 00:34:15,558
I'll be waiting!

386
00:34:16,934 --> 00:34:17,935
Mom.

387
00:34:18,770 --> 00:34:19,854
Don't go.

388
00:34:51,385 --> 00:34:52,553
You're still up?

389
00:34:52,637 --> 00:34:53,846
I can't sleep.

390
00:34:53,930 --> 00:34:56,516
I'll wait a bit more then take some sleeping pills.

391
00:34:56,599 --> 00:34:58,101
What were you doing?

392
00:35:00,478 --> 00:35:01,896
Those were happy times.

393
00:35:01,979 --> 00:35:03,189
I agree.

394
00:35:03,272 --> 00:35:05,108
But I only

395
00:35:06,192 --> 00:35:07,568
realized that now.

396
00:35:14,575 --> 00:35:15,743
Let's go to bed now.

397
00:35:17,787 --> 00:35:19,080
I'm okay now.

398
00:35:20,581 --> 00:35:24,710
We loved this beach so much that we visited every year.

399
00:35:25,253 --> 00:35:26,587
But we never went back

400
00:35:27,213 --> 00:35:29,215
after that incident.

401
00:35:29,298 --> 00:35:30,508
You're right.

402
00:35:34,637 --> 00:35:35,638
Hold on.

403
00:35:36,472 --> 00:35:37,473
What is it?

404
00:35:37,932 --> 00:35:39,642
He's good at swimming too.

405
00:35:39,725 --> 00:35:41,477
Right. Look here.

406
00:35:41,561 --> 00:35:43,688
He even went to a children's Marine Corps Camp.

407
00:35:43,771 --> 00:35:46,315
He once even saved a kid from drowning.

408
00:35:52,989 --> 00:35:54,073
What is it?

409
00:35:55,032 --> 00:35:55,867
I think

410
00:35:56,826 --> 00:35:59,662
I recognize this beach.

411
00:35:59,745 --> 00:36:01,914
Yes, this was the place.

412
00:36:03,207 --> 00:36:04,041
Wait.

413
00:36:04,667 --> 00:36:06,085
Why didn't I recognize it?

414
00:36:06,169 --> 00:36:07,295
What do you mean?

415
00:36:07,378 --> 00:36:08,421
-I-- -Seon-hwa!

416
00:36:09,755 --> 00:36:10,756
Beom-jun!

417
00:36:12,884 --> 00:36:14,051
I have bad news.

418
00:36:24,103 --> 00:36:25,021
Hey, sweetie.

419
00:36:28,482 --> 00:36:29,692
Goodness.

420
00:36:29,775 --> 00:36:30,735
Look…

421
00:36:31,903 --> 00:36:32,737
We're…

422
00:36:34,697 --> 00:36:35,531
Hyun-woo's…

423
00:36:36,490 --> 00:36:37,325
parents.

424
00:36:38,492 --> 00:36:39,327
I see.

425
00:36:43,664 --> 00:36:44,498
I'm sorry.

426
00:36:50,379 --> 00:36:51,464
I'm sorry.

427
00:36:58,554 --> 00:36:59,388
What's going on?

428
00:37:00,097 --> 00:37:01,432
The police said

429
00:37:02,391 --> 00:37:04,769
he was shot.

430
00:37:06,562 --> 00:37:07,396
Yes.

431
00:37:08,022 --> 00:37:09,357
It was because of me.

432
00:37:09,440 --> 00:37:11,317
He took the bullet

433
00:37:12,443 --> 00:37:13,402
for me.

434
00:37:34,340 --> 00:37:36,175
It's okay. Don't cry.

435
00:37:37,677 --> 00:37:38,678
Hyun-woo…

436
00:37:40,221 --> 00:37:41,472
will be okay.

437
00:37:45,017 --> 00:37:46,978
So don't cry.

438
00:37:47,061 --> 00:37:49,063
I'm sorry…

439
00:38:11,961 --> 00:38:14,588
I had two sons,

440
00:38:15,339 --> 00:38:17,091
but one died when he was little.

441
00:38:18,175 --> 00:38:21,929
I thought he died while trying to save Hae-in.

442
00:38:22,013 --> 00:38:23,806
It wasn't her fault.

443
00:38:25,141 --> 00:38:27,435
But I resented her.

444
00:38:30,730 --> 00:38:32,273
I was pathetic

445
00:38:33,774 --> 00:38:34,775
and stupid.

446
00:38:44,243 --> 00:38:46,537
Do you remember what you told me last time?

447
00:38:46,620 --> 00:38:51,500
You said Hyun-woo once saved a kid at a Marine Corps Camp.

448
00:38:51,584 --> 00:38:52,835
Yes, I did.

449
00:38:52,918 --> 00:38:54,420
A boat had malfunctioned,

450
00:38:55,254 --> 00:38:56,964
and he saved a girl…

451
00:39:00,134 --> 00:39:03,512
Both the location and the date looked familiar.

452
00:39:03,596 --> 00:39:06,807
I found it a bit odd.

453
00:39:20,613 --> 00:39:21,739
I'll stitch it up.

454
00:39:24,325 --> 00:39:25,326
His BP is dropping.

455
00:39:26,077 --> 00:39:27,787
-Cardiac arrest! -Get the defibrillator.

456
00:39:27,870 --> 00:39:29,538
-Administer the epinephrine. -Yes, sir.

457
00:39:36,712 --> 00:39:39,340
I believe it was the same beach.

458
00:39:39,423 --> 00:39:40,925
Don't go there.

459
00:39:41,008 --> 00:39:43,511
-What's going on? -Hurry up!

460
00:39:43,594 --> 00:39:46,097
-What's going on? -What's happening?

461
00:39:46,180 --> 00:39:47,181
Hae-in!

462
00:39:48,557 --> 00:39:49,892
Hae-in!

463
00:39:50,893 --> 00:39:52,395
Hae-in!

464
00:40:44,530 --> 00:40:47,199
There she is!

465
00:40:47,283 --> 00:40:48,451
Turn the boat around!

466
00:40:48,534 --> 00:40:49,535
Turn around!

467
00:40:52,204 --> 00:40:53,914
It was Hyun-woo…

468
00:40:57,543 --> 00:40:58,711
who had saved Hae-in.

469
00:41:10,598 --> 00:41:13,184
Su-wan…

470
00:41:13,767 --> 00:41:16,061
No, Su-wan…

471
00:41:17,396 --> 00:41:19,565
Su-wan, please!

472
00:41:21,233 --> 00:41:22,610
My poor son!

473
00:41:24,737 --> 00:41:25,988
Unbelievable.

474
00:41:26,739 --> 00:41:28,657
Talk about an intertwined fate.

475
00:41:29,867 --> 00:41:30,701
I agree.

476
00:41:32,286 --> 00:41:34,288
I was too overwhelmed by grief

477
00:41:34,371 --> 00:41:36,999
to notice Hae-in in pain.

478
00:41:37,833 --> 00:41:41,462
I never thought someone could've saved her.

479
00:41:44,465 --> 00:41:46,217
I had no idea the one who saved her

480
00:41:47,927 --> 00:41:50,012
was with us all along.

481
00:41:50,095 --> 00:41:53,015
I resented him, hurt him, and gave him a tough time.

482
00:41:54,600 --> 00:41:55,601
That's what I did.

483
00:42:01,106 --> 00:42:02,691
It's all in the past.

484
00:42:04,818 --> 00:42:07,613
Let bygones be bygones.

485
00:42:09,323 --> 00:42:10,157
For now…

486
00:42:15,287 --> 00:42:16,455
Let's just pray

487
00:42:18,040 --> 00:42:19,542
that Hyun-woo

488
00:42:20,709 --> 00:42:22,461
will pull through.

489
00:42:23,504 --> 00:42:24,338
And…

490
00:42:24,922 --> 00:42:26,840
once he does…

491
00:42:30,177 --> 00:42:32,930
We just need to be grateful.

492
00:42:34,765 --> 00:42:35,599
Right.

493
00:42:38,477 --> 00:42:39,645
I'll do that.

494
00:42:55,244 --> 00:42:59,290
YOON EUN-SUNG

495
00:43:09,717 --> 00:43:11,719
Ma'am, I can't believe this tragedy.

496
00:43:14,096 --> 00:43:16,599
How much of the shares belonged to Eun-sung?

497
00:43:17,266 --> 00:43:18,559
He had 15.9%.

498
00:43:18,642 --> 00:43:19,977
Transfer them to me right away.

499
00:43:20,060 --> 00:43:21,186
Sorry?

500
00:43:22,479 --> 00:43:23,939
I just confirmed it.

501
00:43:24,023 --> 00:43:27,776
My son is dead which means his shares are all mine.

502
00:43:27,860 --> 00:43:28,986
Yes, ma'am.

503
00:43:32,489 --> 00:43:33,324
And…

504
00:43:34,533 --> 00:43:37,703
how many additional shares can I buy with the secret fund?

505
00:43:37,786 --> 00:43:39,538
You could purchase 7%.

506
00:43:39,622 --> 00:43:42,207
But will Pione Investment want to join hands with us?

507
00:43:42,291 --> 00:43:43,500
What's their goal?

508
00:43:43,584 --> 00:43:45,753
They want to destroy Queens Group, sell everything,

509
00:43:45,836 --> 00:43:47,254
and leave with a profit.

510
00:43:47,338 --> 00:43:50,215
Tell them that we'll sell everything in a year

511
00:43:50,299 --> 00:43:51,342
and let them leave.

512
00:43:51,425 --> 00:43:52,593
They won't refuse then.

513
00:43:53,719 --> 00:43:54,553
Yes, ma'am.

514
00:43:56,221 --> 00:43:58,849
Eun-sung was the one who caused all the issues.

515
00:43:58,932 --> 00:44:00,267
They have nothing to do with me,

516
00:44:00,351 --> 00:44:02,853
so they can't stop me from becoming chairwoman.

517
00:44:03,646 --> 00:44:05,272
Yes, that's correct.

518
00:44:05,356 --> 00:44:07,107
My inauguration

519
00:44:08,192 --> 00:44:09,318
will be grand.

520
00:44:13,697 --> 00:44:15,699
We successfully stitched up the wound.

521
00:44:15,783 --> 00:44:16,867
He lost a lot of blood

522
00:44:16,950 --> 00:44:19,953
and was already suffering from rib fractures.

523
00:44:20,037 --> 00:44:22,498
The surgery was lengthy due to the urgency.

524
00:44:22,581 --> 00:44:24,541
But he pulled through.

525
00:44:25,292 --> 00:44:28,420
However, he has yet to regain consciousness.

526
00:44:28,504 --> 00:44:29,630
We'll need to monitor him.

527
00:44:30,756 --> 00:44:31,799
-Thank you. -Thank you.

528
00:44:33,759 --> 00:44:34,968
Thank God.

529
00:44:35,052 --> 00:44:36,804
-You should go. -No, we're staying.

530
00:44:37,888 --> 00:44:38,972
-Hyun-woo. -Don't.

531
00:44:39,056 --> 00:44:41,016
Thank you.

532
00:44:47,189 --> 00:44:48,148
So where's the file?

533
00:44:48,232 --> 00:44:49,483
It's in my drawer.

534
00:44:50,567 --> 00:44:52,152
The passcode is your birthday.

535
00:45:19,012 --> 00:45:19,972
Come on.

536
00:45:22,933 --> 00:45:24,727
Why aren't you waking up yet?

537
00:45:26,520 --> 00:45:29,189
Can't you see that I'm waiting for you?

538
00:45:30,315 --> 00:45:31,692
I was very worried.

539
00:45:32,735 --> 00:45:33,610
I missed you too.

540
00:45:33,694 --> 00:45:34,778
I feel uneasy.

541
00:45:34,862 --> 00:45:36,321
I'm uncomfortable.

542
00:45:36,405 --> 00:45:38,866
So please resign and find a new job.

543
00:45:38,949 --> 00:45:40,409
I really don't want

544
00:45:40,492 --> 00:45:41,452
to see you.

545
00:45:42,536 --> 00:45:43,620
What's with that look?

546
00:45:43,704 --> 00:45:46,623
You left me high and dry.

547
00:45:46,707 --> 00:45:48,500
Do you think you can seduce me now

548
00:45:48,584 --> 00:45:50,210
since I lost my memory?

549
00:45:50,294 --> 00:45:51,295
Is that it?

550
00:45:54,214 --> 00:45:56,258
I haven't apologized yet.

551
00:45:58,802 --> 00:46:00,929
I haven't regained all my memory,

552
00:46:01,722 --> 00:46:02,931
but I think I know why

553
00:46:03,724 --> 00:46:07,311
my heart ached as soon as I saw you.

554
00:46:08,437 --> 00:46:10,481
I get why I made up excuses

555
00:46:11,440 --> 00:46:12,816
to see you.

556
00:46:16,278 --> 00:46:18,655
The past doesn't matter.

557
00:46:20,032 --> 00:46:23,076
What's important is that we're back together.

558
00:46:24,995 --> 00:46:27,623
So please wake up.

559
00:46:28,624 --> 00:46:30,501
Hear me out…

560
00:46:33,045 --> 00:46:35,172
and tell me that everything is okay.

561
00:46:37,925 --> 00:46:41,470
I'm worried sick right now…

562
00:46:45,098 --> 00:46:46,892
and I miss you so much.

563
00:47:33,397 --> 00:47:36,859
I've only had water for the past 24 hours or more.

564
00:47:38,527 --> 00:47:40,821
I'm serious. I didn't eat.

565
00:47:40,904 --> 00:47:42,155
I didn't sleep either.

566
00:47:44,199 --> 00:47:45,200
Just watch me.

567
00:47:46,076 --> 00:47:48,537
I'm going to keep going until you wake up.

568
00:47:49,162 --> 00:47:52,249
You sacrificed yourself to save me,

569
00:47:52,875 --> 00:47:55,919
and you still haven't regained consciousness.

570
00:47:56,503 --> 00:47:59,089
So how could I possibly eat or sleep?

571
00:48:00,257 --> 00:48:01,383
You didn't forget, did you?

572
00:48:01,466 --> 00:48:03,886
I still need treatment. I need to be careful.

573
00:48:03,969 --> 00:48:05,804
I might as well overstrain myself

574
00:48:05,888 --> 00:48:07,806
and collapse.

575
00:48:10,767 --> 00:48:12,728
I'm a bit dizzy right now

576
00:48:13,520 --> 00:48:16,106
because I cried so much.

577
00:48:24,990 --> 00:48:26,867
Will you still not wake up?

578
00:48:33,457 --> 00:48:35,167
Hyun-woo, are you awake?

579
00:48:35,709 --> 00:48:36,752
Mr. Baek.

580
00:48:45,636 --> 00:48:48,639
Well done. Thank you so much.

581
00:48:51,808 --> 00:48:52,643
Hae-in.

582
00:48:53,393 --> 00:48:54,394
No.

583
00:48:54,478 --> 00:48:55,896
Don't try to talk.

584
00:48:56,396 --> 00:48:58,357
Wait. I'll call the doctor.

585
00:49:05,530 --> 00:49:06,531
Are you okay?

586
00:49:12,663 --> 00:49:13,497
Come on.

587
00:49:14,039 --> 00:49:16,458
You're making me feel worse.

588
00:49:17,376 --> 00:49:19,252
Why are you still worried about me

589
00:49:19,336 --> 00:49:20,712
when you almost died?

590
00:49:21,254 --> 00:49:22,756
I'm okay.

591
00:49:31,765 --> 00:49:32,599
Look.

592
00:49:35,185 --> 00:49:36,603
I'm so sorry

593
00:49:37,688 --> 00:49:39,356
that I failed to recognize you.

594
00:49:39,439 --> 00:49:41,191
I couldn't remember anything

595
00:49:41,274 --> 00:49:43,151
and only said harsh things to you.

596
00:49:43,235 --> 00:49:44,361
Me too.

597
00:49:46,321 --> 00:49:48,115
I forgot too.

598
00:49:49,783 --> 00:49:53,370
I forgot how much I loved you.

599
00:49:53,996 --> 00:49:55,664
I forgot how I promised

600
00:49:55,747 --> 00:49:57,207
to be with you

601
00:49:58,375 --> 00:50:01,545
through thick and thin.

602
00:50:04,339 --> 00:50:05,465
I forgot everything.

603
00:50:09,386 --> 00:50:10,887
I caused you pain.

604
00:50:14,224 --> 00:50:15,058
I'm sorry.

605
00:50:19,730 --> 00:50:21,106
And I love you.

606
00:50:37,414 --> 00:50:38,248
Thank you.

607
00:50:53,555 --> 00:50:54,389
Don't cry.

608
00:51:09,905 --> 00:51:10,739
Hyun-woo.

609
00:51:10,822 --> 00:51:12,616
Gosh. Hyun-woo.

610
00:51:13,700 --> 00:51:15,452
-My baby. -Hyun-woo woke up!

611
00:51:15,535 --> 00:51:16,661
My baby.

612
00:51:16,745 --> 00:51:18,121
Is he up?

613
00:51:18,914 --> 00:51:20,957
-Hyun-woo. -Are you okay?

614
00:51:21,041 --> 00:51:22,000
He's okay.

615
00:51:22,084 --> 00:51:24,002
He can speak well too.

616
00:51:24,086 --> 00:51:25,837
-He spoke? -Yes.

617
00:51:25,921 --> 00:51:27,130
What did he say?

618
00:51:27,214 --> 00:51:28,799
He said, "I love you."

619
00:51:30,258 --> 00:51:31,259
Hyun-woo.

620
00:51:32,052 --> 00:51:33,553
I love you too.

621
00:51:34,805 --> 00:51:35,806
I love you, Hyun-woo.

622
00:51:35,889 --> 00:51:37,265
No.

623
00:51:37,349 --> 00:51:39,476
He said it to Hae-in.

624
00:51:39,559 --> 00:51:42,979
I still love you, Hyun-woo.

625
00:51:44,022 --> 00:51:45,732
-Dad. -He's still in recovery.

626
00:51:45,816 --> 00:51:46,733
He's still in pain.

627
00:51:46,817 --> 00:51:47,984
You shouldn't hug him.

628
00:51:48,068 --> 00:51:48,944
I love you.

629
00:51:49,027 --> 00:51:50,987
-Doctor. -Well done.

630
00:51:51,696 --> 00:51:54,950
Hyun-woo.

631
00:51:56,326 --> 00:51:57,577
Well done.

632
00:52:02,207 --> 00:52:03,166
Gosh.

633
00:52:03,250 --> 00:52:05,127
A shootout in Korea?

634
00:52:05,210 --> 00:52:06,670
I don't know if this is a company

635
00:52:06,753 --> 00:52:08,421
or a drama set.

636
00:52:08,505 --> 00:52:09,339
I'm so flustered.

637
00:52:09,422 --> 00:52:11,883
I'd say this is more like a historical drama.

638
00:52:12,759 --> 00:52:14,886
-What do you mean? -As a history major,

639
00:52:14,970 --> 00:52:17,639
I see this as a battle for the throne.

640
00:52:17,722 --> 00:52:19,391
They kill and spark a bloodbath.

641
00:52:19,474 --> 00:52:20,559
You're wrong.

642
00:52:20,642 --> 00:52:21,726
This is a melodrama.

643
00:52:21,810 --> 00:52:23,353
Like The Dark Knight.

644
00:52:23,436 --> 00:52:25,647
-That's not a melodrama. -Yes, it is.

645
00:52:25,730 --> 00:52:27,566
Batman goes through so much

646
00:52:27,649 --> 00:52:28,817
just to protect his woman

647
00:52:28,900 --> 00:52:30,235
and his beloved city.

648
00:52:30,318 --> 00:52:31,403
Or even Titanic.

649
00:52:31,987 --> 00:52:33,280
Jack sacrifices himself

650
00:52:33,363 --> 00:52:35,699
for the woman he loves…

651
00:52:37,033 --> 00:52:37,868
Whatever.

652
00:52:37,951 --> 00:52:39,786
I'm not interested anyway.

653
00:52:40,620 --> 00:52:41,913
How do you think it'll pan out?

654
00:52:41,997 --> 00:52:45,125
Do you think the Queens family will take back the throne?

655
00:52:45,208 --> 00:52:47,169
What is it? Are you worried?

656
00:52:47,252 --> 00:52:49,296
I hope you stayed in touch with Mr. Hong Soo-cheol.

657
00:52:49,379 --> 00:52:51,047
Is it too late now?

658
00:52:51,131 --> 00:52:52,007
Of course.

659
00:52:52,090 --> 00:52:54,843
Anyway, I learned

660
00:52:54,926 --> 00:52:58,096
abstract nouns like love, friendship,

661
00:52:58,180 --> 00:53:00,140
faithfulness, and loyalty

662
00:53:00,807 --> 00:53:02,434
may not be visible,

663
00:53:02,517 --> 00:53:04,102
but they definitely exist.

664
00:53:04,811 --> 00:53:07,272
Plus, they're the most powerful.

665
00:53:16,948 --> 00:53:18,783
It was too hectic last time to greet you.

666
00:53:18,867 --> 00:53:21,244
I'm Hyun-woo's friend.

667
00:53:21,328 --> 00:53:22,204
I'm Kim Yang-gi.

668
00:53:23,163 --> 00:53:24,539
-I know. -You do?

669
00:53:24,623 --> 00:53:25,832
He briefly wrote

670
00:53:25,916 --> 00:53:28,501
about those around him in his notebook.

671
00:53:28,585 --> 00:53:29,544
I see.

672
00:53:29,628 --> 00:53:30,754
What did he write?

673
00:53:30,837 --> 00:53:32,672
That you were his divorce attorney.

674
00:53:32,756 --> 00:53:33,715
I see.

675
00:53:33,798 --> 00:53:35,133
So this isn't an excuse.

676
00:53:35,217 --> 00:53:36,468
Yes, I was his attorney.

677
00:53:36,551 --> 00:53:39,221
But I barely defended and pretty much scolded him.

678
00:53:39,304 --> 00:53:40,472
I tried to dissuade him

679
00:53:41,139 --> 00:53:42,140
from divorcing you.

680
00:53:42,724 --> 00:53:43,725
I see.

681
00:53:44,267 --> 00:53:45,435
By the way,

682
00:53:45,518 --> 00:53:47,771
-why did we get a divorce? -Sorry?

683
00:53:47,854 --> 00:53:50,899
I feel like you'd know best.

684
00:53:52,484 --> 00:53:53,693
Well…

685
00:53:53,777 --> 00:53:57,113
You fell apart due to your busy schedules and decided to stay as friends--

686
00:53:57,197 --> 00:53:59,616
Despite living together?

687
00:53:59,699 --> 00:54:00,533
I know, right?

688
00:54:02,410 --> 00:54:05,747
But I don't think the reason matters anymore.

689
00:54:07,165 --> 00:54:08,166
Sorry?

690
00:54:08,250 --> 00:54:10,377
There's no point in digging into the past.

691
00:54:10,877 --> 00:54:13,380
I think you should just worry about the guy

692
00:54:13,463 --> 00:54:16,091
who was blinded by love

693
00:54:16,800 --> 00:54:18,760
and sacrificed himself for you.

694
00:54:21,972 --> 00:54:23,848
You're a good friend.

695
00:54:23,932 --> 00:54:25,767
Gosh. I'm flattered.

696
00:54:27,102 --> 00:54:30,063
Even I didn't know I was this great of a friend.

697
00:54:30,897 --> 00:54:34,067
But the truth always reveals itself in tough times.

698
00:54:34,150 --> 00:54:35,235
I bet he felt the same way.

699
00:54:35,318 --> 00:54:37,904
He seems to have finally realized

700
00:54:37,988 --> 00:54:39,990
how much he loves you.

701
00:54:40,073 --> 00:54:42,367
Don't compliment me!

702
00:54:43,034 --> 00:54:44,661
Are you really dying or what?

703
00:54:46,162 --> 00:54:47,872
You don't know anything, do you?

704
00:54:49,165 --> 00:54:50,166
I'm going there…

705
00:54:52,335 --> 00:54:53,962
because I want to be happy.

706
00:54:54,838 --> 00:54:56,840
I won't be able to live with it

707
00:54:58,008 --> 00:54:59,467
if something happened to her…

708
00:55:02,595 --> 00:55:04,014
or if she got hurt.

709
00:55:06,975 --> 00:55:08,351
You can never predict the future.

710
00:55:08,435 --> 00:55:11,313
You couldn't stand her in the past.

711
00:55:11,980 --> 00:55:13,606
But now, you're head over heels.

712
00:55:14,316 --> 00:55:15,150
You're right.

713
00:55:17,861 --> 00:55:19,070
Who knew?

714
00:55:40,258 --> 00:55:41,092
Hey, Hae-in.

715
00:55:41,718 --> 00:55:43,762
If you don't want to regret it,

716
00:55:43,845 --> 00:55:45,472
don't you dare let Hyun-woo go.

717
00:55:50,435 --> 00:55:53,229
I almost ripped through the paper.

718
00:55:53,313 --> 00:55:54,731
I was in a rush.

719
00:55:55,440 --> 00:55:58,276
I should've just focused on the surgery if my life was on the line.

720
00:55:58,360 --> 00:56:00,278
When did I have the time to worry about him?

721
00:56:07,035 --> 00:56:07,869
But then again…

722
00:56:11,164 --> 00:56:12,582
I get why I was worried.

723
00:56:14,250 --> 00:56:15,251
I understand.

724
00:56:53,665 --> 00:56:55,250
I won't let you let go. I'm still here.

725
00:56:57,794 --> 00:56:59,921
When did he read this?

726
00:57:00,672 --> 00:57:01,673
What a sly…

727
00:57:06,719 --> 00:57:07,554
Mr. Baek.

728
00:57:09,431 --> 00:57:10,390
Wake up.

729
00:57:14,144 --> 00:57:16,521
There's been a misunderstanding.

730
00:57:16,604 --> 00:57:18,815
I didn't write this part.

731
00:57:18,898 --> 00:57:20,692
My old self wrote it

732
00:57:21,901 --> 00:57:23,319
in a hurry.

733
00:57:23,403 --> 00:57:25,155
So why are you replying to me?

734
00:57:26,406 --> 00:57:27,949
What? Did you smile?

735
00:57:28,992 --> 00:57:30,743
I saw everything. Get up right now.

736
00:57:34,122 --> 00:57:36,374
Hey, what is it?

737
00:57:36,458 --> 00:57:37,500
Mr. Baek.

738
00:57:38,084 --> 00:57:39,461
Why are you so cunning?

739
00:57:39,544 --> 00:57:40,795
Who taught you?

740
00:57:43,923 --> 00:57:46,634
Don't make me laugh. It hurts.

741
00:57:46,718 --> 00:57:48,887
Then don't laugh and just answer me.

742
00:57:57,061 --> 00:57:59,147
Should we just go home?

743
00:58:00,190 --> 00:58:01,900
I think we should.

744
00:58:01,983 --> 00:58:02,817
Honey.

745
00:58:04,152 --> 00:58:05,904
What is it?

746
00:58:12,952 --> 00:58:14,704
We should go eat.

747
00:58:15,455 --> 00:58:17,582
-I just had a sandwich. -That's a snack.

748
00:58:17,665 --> 00:58:19,167
-It's not a meal. -Right.

749
00:58:20,001 --> 00:58:22,420
But my bag is still in there.

750
00:58:23,046 --> 00:58:24,839
-It's that blue one next to the bed. -Hey.

751
00:58:24,923 --> 00:58:28,259
Your bag should be the least of your worries.

752
00:58:28,343 --> 00:58:31,554
Love is in the air right now.

753
00:58:32,180 --> 00:58:33,097
Let's just go.

754
00:58:34,057 --> 00:58:36,476
What do you say to some spicy fish stew

755
00:58:36,559 --> 00:58:38,061
-near Namhansanseong? -I'm down!

756
00:58:38,144 --> 00:58:39,395
-Some makgeolli? -Sounds great!

757
00:58:39,479 --> 00:58:41,272
Isn't that really far?

758
00:58:41,356 --> 00:58:42,649
Jeez.

759
00:58:43,149 --> 00:58:44,651
It's still near the capital.

760
00:58:44,734 --> 00:58:45,985
Hurry up!

761
00:58:46,069 --> 00:58:49,113
We always ate around the suburbs

762
00:58:49,197 --> 00:58:50,740
for those lovebirds' sake.

763
00:58:50,823 --> 00:58:51,658
Goodness.

764
00:58:51,741 --> 00:58:52,700
Well done.

765
00:58:52,784 --> 00:58:54,369
Send us the hospital's address.

766
00:58:54,452 --> 00:58:57,413
There's not much we can do except send some side dishes.

767
00:58:58,039 --> 00:58:59,916
-Hospital food isn't great. -I agree.

768
00:58:59,999 --> 00:59:01,918
Ms. Hong isn't fully well either.

769
00:59:02,001 --> 00:59:04,796
What if she falls ill while taking care of him?

770
00:59:05,463 --> 00:59:06,506
I'm still envious.

771
00:59:06,589 --> 00:59:09,551
She's taking care of a man who took a bullet for her.

772
00:59:09,634 --> 00:59:12,345
Plus, he's utterly beautiful.

773
00:59:14,222 --> 00:59:17,642
Whatever. She doesn't remember him.

774
00:59:17,725 --> 00:59:20,603
He's just someone she met recently. Are you really envious?

775
00:59:20,687 --> 00:59:23,064
That's the best part.

776
00:59:23,773 --> 00:59:25,441
-What? -Whether it's three years

777
00:59:25,525 --> 00:59:27,485
or thirty years with your husband,

778
00:59:27,569 --> 00:59:29,195
do you know when you're the happiest?

779
00:59:29,279 --> 00:59:32,323
It's when you're first seeing each other.

780
00:59:32,407 --> 00:59:34,993
When is he the most handsome?

781
00:59:35,076 --> 00:59:37,287
When you barely know him!

782
00:59:38,746 --> 00:59:40,832
The best part is when you're strangers!

783
00:59:51,384 --> 00:59:55,388
You must take me for a fool since I lost my memory.

784
00:59:57,223 --> 00:59:58,474
What do you mean?

785
00:59:58,558 --> 00:59:59,809
Let me rephrase

786
00:59:59,892 --> 01:00:01,894
what you told me.

787
01:00:01,978 --> 01:00:02,812
Not only…

788
01:00:04,856 --> 01:00:06,816
are you handsome and have a nice voice,

789
01:00:06,899 --> 01:00:09,027
but you were the top student at law school.

790
01:00:09,110 --> 01:00:11,321
You were even a boxing champion when you were young.

791
01:00:11,404 --> 01:00:12,989
You joined the Marine Corps--

792
01:00:13,072 --> 01:00:15,908
The Special Guard Team, to be exact.

793
01:00:15,992 --> 01:00:19,829
Exactly. So you're claiming to be

794
01:00:20,663 --> 01:00:22,248
such a perfect guy.

795
01:00:23,791 --> 01:00:25,168
Look here, Mr. Baek.

796
01:00:26,085 --> 01:00:27,837
Yes, I'm looking at you.

797
01:00:30,214 --> 01:00:32,634
I get that you want to impress me,

798
01:00:32,717 --> 01:00:35,219
but you're pushing it. You're too perfect.

799
01:00:35,803 --> 01:00:38,264
I mean… Am I that perfect?

800
01:00:39,015 --> 01:00:41,976
Of course. You have all the traits that I love.

801
01:00:43,061 --> 01:00:46,105
Really? Do you love all of them?

802
01:00:49,067 --> 01:00:53,863
I understand that you like me and want to win my heart once again.

803
01:00:53,946 --> 01:00:56,032
But you should be honest about yourself.

804
01:00:56,115 --> 01:00:58,159
Don't exaggerate and tell me the truth.

805
01:00:58,242 --> 01:00:59,285
It is the truth.

806
01:01:00,078 --> 01:01:02,538
Be honest. You were never a champion, right?

807
01:01:05,625 --> 01:01:06,793
What is this?

808
01:01:06,876 --> 01:01:09,712
I even like the way you laugh.

809
01:01:12,173 --> 01:01:13,925
You know too much about me.

810
01:01:14,717 --> 01:01:17,136
It's unfair since I can't remember anything.

811
01:01:28,731 --> 01:01:30,441
Father, it's me.

812
01:01:31,317 --> 01:01:33,486
Have you finally forgiven me?

813
01:01:33,569 --> 01:01:34,779
I'm sorry.

814
01:01:34,862 --> 01:01:38,991
Father, the three of us have finally gathered together.

815
01:01:40,368 --> 01:01:42,412
Don't you worry anymore.

816
01:01:42,495 --> 01:01:46,165
Now that we've reunited, we'll take back what's ours.

817
01:01:48,459 --> 01:01:49,961
We'll avenge you.

818
01:01:56,050 --> 01:01:58,261
If you look here, she purchased

819
01:01:58,344 --> 01:02:00,972
an additional 7% from non-institutional investors.

820
01:02:01,055 --> 01:02:03,766
Does that make her shares 45.1%?

821
01:02:03,850 --> 01:02:06,686
Our frozen shares are 39.3%.

822
01:02:06,769 --> 01:02:08,771
Will Pione Investment continue to be on her side?

823
01:02:08,855 --> 01:02:11,441
Judging by what I saw in New York, probably.

824
01:02:11,524 --> 01:02:13,401
Their goal is to sell the company

825
01:02:13,484 --> 01:02:16,195
and leave as soon as they can without causing a scene.

826
01:02:16,279 --> 01:02:20,074
-And Seul-hee will make that happen. -Then, we're no match legally.

827
01:02:20,158 --> 01:02:21,659
She's the biggest shareholder.

828
01:02:21,743 --> 01:02:24,954
She bought 13.3% of the shares with the secret fund.

829
01:02:25,037 --> 01:02:26,998
But secret funds are illegal,

830
01:02:27,081 --> 01:02:29,292
and they should be returned to the government.

831
01:02:29,917 --> 01:02:32,211
I'm going to file a nullity suit for it.

832
01:02:38,718 --> 01:02:39,552
Hey!

833
01:02:40,803 --> 01:02:43,347
What do you mean? Why should we turn ourselves in?

834
01:02:43,431 --> 01:02:46,726
Hey, I've done my part.

835
01:02:53,900 --> 01:02:58,070
Hyun-woo told me that Ms. Hong will like these songs.

836
01:02:58,696 --> 01:03:01,699
I doubt she'll remember anything just by listening to them.

837
01:03:01,783 --> 01:03:03,242
He's watched one too many dramas.

838
01:03:03,326 --> 01:03:04,911
He's doing everything he can.

839
01:03:05,745 --> 01:03:08,039
Also, a package will be delivered from Germany.

840
01:03:08,122 --> 01:03:10,833
Make sure she gets it.

841
01:03:10,917 --> 01:03:13,169
Why must I do that?

842
01:03:22,845 --> 01:03:24,180
This is from Germany.

843
01:03:25,264 --> 01:03:29,519
I'll take it. Mr. Yoon wants to check all mails sent to Ms. Hong.

844
01:03:34,148 --> 01:03:36,359
Are these for Mr. Yoon?

845
01:03:36,442 --> 01:03:37,568
I'll take them.

846
01:03:37,652 --> 01:03:39,529
I'm on my way to see him right now.

847
01:03:45,284 --> 01:03:48,496
I was their love messenger.

848
01:03:48,579 --> 01:03:50,039
I'd say I atoned for my sins.

849
01:03:50,122 --> 01:03:51,290
Didn't you hear?

850
01:03:51,374 --> 01:03:53,292
If they want their frozen shares back,

851
01:03:53,376 --> 01:03:56,003
they need to prove that Seul-hee was behind everything.

852
01:03:56,087 --> 01:03:57,171
We're witnesses.

853
01:03:57,255 --> 01:03:58,297
You can do it then.

854
01:03:58,381 --> 01:03:59,799
-Grace. -Hey.

855
01:03:59,882 --> 01:04:03,219
The most useless thing you can do is to go down with someone.

856
01:04:03,302 --> 01:04:05,972
At least let me mourn for you.

857
01:04:07,682 --> 01:04:11,602
Grace, I don't want to live like Eun-sung did.

858
01:04:12,645 --> 01:04:14,313
Don't you pity him?

859
01:04:14,397 --> 01:04:18,192
He was desperate for love all his life but never received it.

860
01:04:18,276 --> 01:04:20,736
Was there anyone with him during his demise?

861
01:04:22,154 --> 01:04:24,240
I want to start living an honest life.

862
01:04:24,323 --> 01:04:25,783
No secrets.

863
01:04:25,867 --> 01:04:27,243
No guilt.

864
01:04:27,326 --> 01:04:28,244
No remorse.

865
01:04:28,911 --> 01:04:30,204
I want

866
01:04:30,830 --> 01:04:32,206
to love

867
01:04:33,249 --> 01:04:34,083
and be loved.

868
01:04:36,377 --> 01:04:37,211
Hey.

869
01:04:38,421 --> 01:04:41,966
Do you think they'll take you in even after you serve time in prison?

870
01:04:42,049 --> 01:04:43,634
Who's going to prison?

871
01:04:52,059 --> 01:04:53,311
EVERGREEN HOPE ORPHANAGE

872
01:04:55,062 --> 01:04:56,272
Answer me.

873
01:04:56,355 --> 01:04:57,565
You're not going anywhere.

874
01:04:57,648 --> 01:04:58,733
Don't do anything stupid.

875
01:04:58,816 --> 01:05:00,985
This is where we first met.

876
01:05:04,030 --> 01:05:06,324
I barely remember. I was so little.

877
01:05:07,450 --> 01:05:09,869
I was really bored here.

878
01:05:10,786 --> 01:05:13,331
The other kids had hope and waited for their moms

879
01:05:13,414 --> 01:05:14,415
to pick them up.

880
01:05:15,374 --> 01:05:16,918
But I had no one to wait for.

881
01:05:18,336 --> 01:05:22,715
My parents didn't even leave a letter or a note with my name on it.

882
01:05:23,549 --> 01:05:26,218
They just left me in an apple crate during the winter.

883
01:05:26,302 --> 01:05:28,512
They definitely had no plans of returning.

884
01:05:30,348 --> 01:05:32,808
Then one day, you appeared.

885
01:05:33,684 --> 01:05:36,979
You visited once every several months, and I waited for you.

886
01:05:39,023 --> 01:05:42,401
Is that when you started having feelings for me?

887
01:05:43,361 --> 01:05:46,113
That's not it. I could only have it when you visited.

888
01:05:47,114 --> 01:05:48,199
Strawberry shortcake.

889
01:05:49,951 --> 01:05:51,243
Da-hye?

890
01:05:52,662 --> 01:05:53,663
Does this mean

891
01:05:54,288 --> 01:05:57,166
I was your first love?

892
01:05:57,249 --> 01:05:59,585
-Is that right? -I was waiting for the cake.

893
01:06:01,295 --> 01:06:02,129
And…

894
01:06:04,632 --> 01:06:05,841
I doubt you recognize this.

895
01:06:06,801 --> 01:06:08,135
It used to be yours.

896
01:06:10,471 --> 01:06:11,555
Really?

897
01:06:12,056 --> 01:06:13,933
And you kept it all these years

898
01:06:14,809 --> 01:06:16,852
as a token

899
01:06:17,520 --> 01:06:18,980
of our love?

900
01:06:20,106 --> 01:06:22,149
This is our never-ending destiny.

901
01:06:22,233 --> 01:06:23,067
Silly.

902
01:06:23,150 --> 01:06:24,819
I took it from you.

903
01:06:28,781 --> 01:06:31,826
I really liked the doll.

904
01:06:32,410 --> 01:06:33,828
Carrying it with me

905
01:06:33,911 --> 01:06:37,331
made me feel like a rich kid who had parents.

906
01:06:38,541 --> 01:06:41,085
It was so soft.

907
01:06:41,168 --> 01:06:42,211
I liked how it felt.

908
01:06:42,837 --> 01:06:45,006
I fell asleep easily even in the cold.

909
01:06:45,089 --> 01:06:47,508
So I wanted to thank you.

910
01:06:47,591 --> 01:06:49,135
But that was it.

911
01:06:49,218 --> 01:06:51,137
You never returned.

912
01:06:52,346 --> 01:06:53,973
So did you wait for me?

913
01:06:55,641 --> 01:06:57,059
Of course.

914
01:06:57,143 --> 01:06:59,603
The chairman gave out the same cake again.

915
01:07:06,193 --> 01:07:07,903
But it wasn't tasty anymore.

916
01:07:14,285 --> 01:07:16,287
Because I was waiting for you.

917
01:07:21,500 --> 01:07:23,335
I waited a long time,

918
01:07:24,754 --> 01:07:26,797
so it's your turn now.

919
01:07:29,133 --> 01:07:30,051
I'll be back.

920
01:07:31,093 --> 01:07:32,970
I need to do this to lift the burden.

921
01:07:33,054 --> 01:07:34,346
Da-hye.

922
01:07:35,514 --> 01:07:36,599
No.

923
01:07:36,682 --> 01:07:38,059
Please take care of Geon-u.

924
01:07:39,810 --> 01:07:42,104
I promise to be good forever

925
01:07:42,730 --> 01:07:44,231
once I return.

926
01:07:44,315 --> 01:07:47,234
I'll be a loyal, kind wife.

927
01:07:47,318 --> 01:07:48,444
Don't be ridiculous.

928
01:07:48,527 --> 01:07:51,614
Do you think I'll let you do this?

929
01:07:51,697 --> 01:07:55,284
I'm going to hire the best attorneys in the country.

930
01:07:56,035 --> 01:07:59,205
I'll spend all my money if I have to.

931
01:07:59,288 --> 01:08:00,498
I refuse to say goodbye!

932
01:08:02,333 --> 01:08:03,417
I don't want to.

933
01:08:04,126 --> 01:08:05,586
Soo-cheol, please.

934
01:08:09,215 --> 01:08:10,925
Stop talking.

935
01:08:23,354 --> 01:08:24,230
COURT

936
01:08:24,313 --> 01:08:25,815
Eun-sung, the defendant's late son,

937
01:08:25,898 --> 01:08:28,818
laundered 900 billion won of secret funds through his shell company

938
01:08:28,901 --> 01:08:30,820
and spent it on Queens Group's shares.

939
01:08:30,903 --> 01:08:33,572
After his death, the defendant received his shares

940
01:08:33,656 --> 01:08:35,741
and spent the rest of the fund on more shares.

941
01:08:35,825 --> 01:08:38,244
She acquired a total of 13.3% of the shares.

942
01:08:38,327 --> 01:08:42,957
Our plaintiffs would like to file a nullity suit regarding the 13.3%

943
01:08:43,040 --> 01:08:45,126
that the defendant acquired illegally.

944
01:08:45,209 --> 01:08:48,087
The defendant's counselor may give their response.

945
01:08:49,213 --> 01:08:52,675
Our defendant legally inherited the shares and money

946
01:08:52,758 --> 01:08:55,261
previously owned by her late son

947
01:08:55,344 --> 01:08:56,595
through the law of succession.

948
01:08:56,679 --> 01:08:59,306
It hasn't even been a month since she lost her son.

949
01:08:59,390 --> 01:09:02,351
It is inhumane for the plaintiffs to file a suit against her

950
01:09:02,434 --> 01:09:05,521
to take control of the company when she's still mourning.

951
01:09:05,604 --> 01:09:08,065
The defendant, Moh, committed a two-trillion-won scam

952
01:09:08,149 --> 01:09:10,401
in order to take over Queens Group.

953
01:09:10,484 --> 01:09:13,237
She encouraged people to purchase a problematic piece of land.

954
01:09:13,320 --> 01:09:15,531
Once the construction begins,

955
01:09:15,614 --> 01:09:17,449
we'll insinuate the licensing issue

956
01:09:17,533 --> 01:09:20,411
related to altitude restrictions to the investors.

957
01:09:20,494 --> 01:09:24,373
She successfully made the plaintiffs invest in the scam by fabricating

958
01:09:24,456 --> 01:09:26,917
the business profit by fivefold.

959
01:09:27,001 --> 01:09:28,878
Plus, she created a double contract

960
01:09:28,961 --> 01:09:31,505
to make it seem like the plaintiffs were behind it.

961
01:09:31,589 --> 01:09:35,217
As a result, the landowners filed a suit against the plaintiffs.

962
01:09:35,301 --> 01:09:38,179
I'd like to submit related evidence, records of the proceedings

963
01:09:38,262 --> 01:09:41,015
regarding relocation of the army base, the land purchase plan,

964
01:09:41,098 --> 01:09:43,350
and proof of the fabricated business profit.

965
01:09:44,268 --> 01:09:45,227
All of these charges

966
01:09:45,311 --> 01:09:49,023
are related to Mr. Yoon Eun-sung, the defendant's late son.

967
01:09:49,106 --> 01:09:52,568
They have nothing to do with her nor is there evidence to back it up.

968
01:09:52,651 --> 01:09:53,611
Your Honor.

969
01:09:53,694 --> 01:09:55,696
My son and I have been apart for 20 years.

970
01:09:55,779 --> 01:09:57,156
So how would I have known

971
01:09:58,073 --> 01:10:00,492
that he had schemed all this?

972
01:10:00,576 --> 01:10:03,829
Please understand that I am still grieving

973
01:10:04,663 --> 01:10:06,123
the loss of my son

974
01:10:06,749 --> 01:10:10,211
and can't elaborate any further.

975
01:10:12,254 --> 01:10:15,549
I'd like to bring a witness to the stand who will prove that she's lying.

976
01:10:19,470 --> 01:10:21,055
I hid my identity

977
01:10:21,722 --> 01:10:24,934
and married Hong Soo-cheol like the defendant told me to.

978
01:10:25,017 --> 01:10:27,686
I provided her with intimate information,

979
01:10:27,770 --> 01:10:29,980
introduced Yoon Eun-sung to Hong Soo-cheol,

980
01:10:30,064 --> 01:10:33,067
and persuaded my husband to invest in the scam.

981
01:10:33,859 --> 01:10:36,570
Do you have proof that the defendant

982
01:10:36,654 --> 01:10:37,738
gave you those orders?

983
01:10:37,821 --> 01:10:39,156
I…

984
01:10:40,199 --> 01:10:41,116
do not.

985
01:10:41,200 --> 01:10:43,035
The defendant and I rarely met

986
01:10:43,118 --> 01:10:45,079
since she was very cautious.

987
01:10:45,162 --> 01:10:47,289
She made others give me her orders.

988
01:10:47,373 --> 01:10:50,668
The witness is currently under investigation for fraud.

989
01:10:50,751 --> 01:10:52,711
Please keep in mind that she could commit perjury

990
01:10:52,795 --> 01:10:54,505
for a mitigation of punishment, Your Honor.

991
01:10:56,048 --> 01:10:58,217
Defendant, you may say your closing statement.

992
01:10:59,927 --> 01:11:03,764
Your Honor, what could I possibly want when I've lost my son?

993
01:11:04,431 --> 01:11:06,976
The late chairman handed over his company to me

994
01:11:08,018 --> 01:11:10,354
because he couldn't trust his own family.

995
01:11:10,437 --> 01:11:12,064
He wanted me

996
01:11:12,147 --> 01:11:14,149
to protect it,

997
01:11:14,233 --> 01:11:16,485
and that's all I want to do.

998
01:11:27,746 --> 01:11:29,164
Your Honor.

999
01:11:29,248 --> 01:11:30,874
I'd like to request Ms. Hong Hae-in,

1000
01:11:30,958 --> 01:11:33,127
one of our plaintiffs, to give a closing statement.

1001
01:11:33,836 --> 01:11:34,670
She may do so.

1002
01:11:41,677 --> 01:11:42,594
Three weeks ago,

1003
01:11:43,345 --> 01:11:46,557
I was kidnapped and confined by the defendant's son.

1004
01:11:46,640 --> 01:11:49,435
That's when I overheard the two talking.

1005
01:11:49,518 --> 01:11:51,478
The proof that you killed the chairman?

1006
01:11:51,562 --> 01:11:53,856
If Hae-in had also died back then,

1007
01:11:53,939 --> 01:11:57,359
you wouldn't have disrupted my plan in this manner.

1008
01:11:57,443 --> 01:11:58,444
That's my only regret.

1009
01:11:58,527 --> 01:12:01,989
That's when I found out that the boat accident 25 years ago

1010
01:12:02,072 --> 01:12:06,160
and the death of my grandfather was all related to the defendant.

1011
01:12:17,171 --> 01:12:18,380
Goodness.

1012
01:12:19,048 --> 01:12:19,923
How dare you?

1013
01:12:21,133 --> 01:12:24,345
Hae-in, what are you saying?

1014
01:12:25,721 --> 01:12:27,723
I'm innocent, Your Honor.

1015
01:12:30,684 --> 01:12:34,480
Your Honor, the plaintiff recently received brain surgery.

1016
01:12:34,563 --> 01:12:36,315
-There's no proof. -Yes, there is.

1017
01:12:39,818 --> 01:12:42,446
This evidence will support her statement.

1018
01:12:54,291 --> 01:12:56,835
Your Honor, that evidence wasn't submitted in advance.

1019
01:12:56,919 --> 01:12:58,212
You wanted evidence.

1020
01:12:58,837 --> 01:13:00,089
I'll accept it.

1021
01:13:19,066 --> 01:13:21,443
Wait. That…

1022
01:13:21,527 --> 01:13:23,237
Why…

1023
01:13:44,842 --> 01:13:46,927
Gosh, I don't know anymore.

1024
01:13:47,594 --> 01:13:48,470
Is this it?

1025
01:13:48,554 --> 01:13:50,597
I made a copy

1026
01:13:50,681 --> 01:13:51,849
and put it back.

1027
01:13:51,932 --> 01:13:53,434
She won't know that we swapped it.

1028
01:14:00,816 --> 01:14:03,819
Your Honor! Wait. Please stop the video.

1029
01:14:03,902 --> 01:14:05,070
No, you're probably not okay.

1030
01:14:05,154 --> 01:14:08,198
That's what the drug does. Ten minutes in the respiratory system,

1031
01:14:08,282 --> 01:14:10,492
-and you'll slowly become paralyzed. -You…

1032
01:14:10,576 --> 01:14:12,995
You bitch. I'll kill you.

1033
01:14:13,078 --> 01:14:14,246
You… Father…

1034
01:14:14,329 --> 01:14:15,914
-Don't worry. -Father…

1035
01:14:15,998 --> 01:14:17,458
You won't die right away.

1036
01:14:18,125 --> 01:14:19,751
If you do,

1037
01:14:20,961 --> 01:14:22,045
this will be useless.

1038
01:14:22,129 --> 01:14:25,090
I can only become your legal guardian

1039
01:14:25,174 --> 01:14:29,511
and have a say if you're in a coma.

1040
01:14:29,595 --> 01:14:30,471
So…

1041
01:14:31,180 --> 01:14:32,347
be in a coma

1042
01:14:32,431 --> 01:14:35,392
for two to three months before you die.

1043
01:14:35,476 --> 01:14:37,102
Can you do that for me?

1044
01:14:50,699 --> 01:14:53,452
It's… It's not true.

1045
01:14:53,535 --> 01:14:54,369
Unbelievable.

1046
01:14:55,454 --> 01:14:56,914
It's fabricated.

1047
01:14:56,997 --> 01:14:58,248
That's not me.

1048
01:14:59,416 --> 01:15:00,918
Say something!

1049
01:15:06,423 --> 01:15:09,343
Please understand that she needs to be arrested right now

1050
01:15:09,426 --> 01:15:10,552
since she has a history

1051
01:15:10,636 --> 01:15:13,597
of disguising herself and could flee.

1052
01:15:14,640 --> 01:15:15,724
Ms. Moh Seul-hee.

1053
01:15:15,807 --> 01:15:17,476
You're under arrest for attempted murder.

1054
01:15:17,559 --> 01:15:20,270
You may hire an attorney and file a complaint

1055
01:15:20,354 --> 01:15:21,855
if you deem this arrest unjust.

1056
01:15:21,939 --> 01:15:23,565
Why me? No!

1057
01:15:23,649 --> 01:15:25,817
-Grab her. -What did I do?

1058
01:15:27,819 --> 01:15:31,490
I'm innocent! What did I do so wrong?

1059
01:15:31,573 --> 01:15:33,033
What did I do?

1060
01:15:33,116 --> 01:15:34,076
I'm innocent!

1061
01:15:34,159 --> 01:15:35,994
Let me go! I'm innocent!

1062
01:15:36,078 --> 01:15:37,246
This is unfair!

1063
01:15:37,746 --> 01:15:40,707
What did I do so wrong? I'm innocent!

1064
01:15:40,791 --> 01:15:43,669
What did I do to you guys?

1065
01:15:43,752 --> 01:15:45,671
Let me go! Hey!

1066
01:15:45,754 --> 01:15:48,632
Let me go! Damn it!

1067
01:15:48,715 --> 01:15:49,591
Let me go! No!

1068
01:15:49,675 --> 01:15:52,761
The Queens Group's family has been reinstated.

1069
01:15:52,844 --> 01:15:55,764
The family filed a nullity suit

1070
01:15:55,847 --> 01:15:57,683
against Moh Seul-hee, the domestic partner

1071
01:15:57,766 --> 01:15:59,560
of the late Chairman Hong Man-dae.

1072
01:15:59,643 --> 01:16:02,563
Baek Hyun-woo, the plaintiffs' attorney,

1073
01:16:02,646 --> 01:16:04,856
successfully proved that the late Yoon Eun-sung

1074
01:16:04,940 --> 01:16:07,818
and Moh Seul-hee were behind the investment fraud.

1075
01:16:07,901 --> 01:16:10,445
As a result, the family reclaimed

1076
01:16:10,529 --> 01:16:13,323
all of their lost shares from Pione Investment

1077
01:16:13,407 --> 01:16:17,035
and the joint surety.

1078
01:16:17,119 --> 01:16:20,414
Those related to the fraud were also convicted.

1079
01:16:23,667 --> 01:16:26,128
A video recording of Moh Seul-hee poisoning

1080
01:16:26,211 --> 01:16:29,965
the late chairman was submitted as evidence during the trial,

1081
01:16:30,048 --> 01:16:31,258
shocking the public.

1082
01:16:31,341 --> 01:16:32,759
-Call my attorney! -Moh was arrested

1083
01:16:32,843 --> 01:16:34,261
-for attempted murder. -Call him!

1084
01:16:34,344 --> 01:16:36,305
-Call my attorney! -She's also being investigated

1085
01:16:36,388 --> 01:16:37,681
for investment fraud,

1086
01:16:37,764 --> 01:16:40,559
violations of foreign exchange transaction laws, and identity theft.

1087
01:16:42,019 --> 01:16:44,479
Hey, be quiet.

1088
01:16:44,563 --> 01:16:46,607
You're being too noisy.

1089
01:16:47,482 --> 01:16:49,109
Damn it.

1090
01:16:49,192 --> 01:16:51,570
Let me go.

1091
01:16:51,653 --> 01:16:53,196
Grab her!

1092
01:16:53,280 --> 01:16:55,324
-Hey! -Let me go!

1093
01:17:03,957 --> 01:17:05,125
Hey.

1094
01:17:09,212 --> 01:17:10,422
Stomp on her.

1095
01:17:14,635 --> 01:17:15,886
That's enough.

1096
01:18:05,769 --> 01:18:07,229
Where's everyone?

1097
01:18:07,312 --> 01:18:10,524
Hae-in went to look at documents before officially going back to work.

1098
01:18:10,607 --> 01:18:12,693
And Soo-cheol… Well, it's obvious.

1099
01:18:12,776 --> 01:18:14,444
He's bawling. Let him be.

1100
01:18:14,528 --> 01:18:17,322
He'll be sobbing for some time after sending his wife away.

1101
01:18:22,911 --> 01:18:28,542
Okay. Here comes the plane.

1102
01:18:29,167 --> 01:18:30,961
You eat so well.

1103
01:18:32,462 --> 01:18:33,964
HONG GEON-U, SOO-CHEOL, DA-HYE

1104
01:18:34,047 --> 01:18:36,800
Let's grow strong

1105
01:18:37,843 --> 01:18:39,219
until Mom comes.

1106
01:18:41,263 --> 01:18:42,806
-And Beom-ja? -Beats me.

1107
01:18:42,889 --> 01:18:46,810
She got all dolled up and left after getting a text.

1108
01:18:46,893 --> 01:18:48,854
Jeez, he's so spontaneous.

1109
01:18:48,937 --> 01:18:50,689
Why does he suddenly want to meet?

1110
01:18:50,772 --> 01:18:53,692
Gosh, I shouldn't have drunk yesterday.

1111
01:18:53,775 --> 01:18:58,196
I'm so bloated. Where are my double eyelids?

1112
01:19:05,454 --> 01:19:06,663
Did you get lost?

1113
01:19:06,747 --> 01:19:09,458
I purposely chose the highest building so it'd be easier to find.

1114
01:19:09,541 --> 01:19:11,543
You're right. I saw the building,

1115
01:19:11,626 --> 01:19:14,129
but it took me some time to find my way here.

1116
01:19:14,212 --> 01:19:15,505
I'm sorry for suddenly calling.

1117
01:19:15,589 --> 01:19:17,924
I liked it. My heart raced.

1118
01:19:24,014 --> 01:19:26,057
I have something to say.

1119
01:19:27,017 --> 01:19:27,934
I'm listening.

1120
01:19:38,028 --> 01:19:39,237
Thank you.

1121
01:19:51,124 --> 01:19:55,462
As you already know, we are very different.

1122
01:19:57,506 --> 01:19:58,507
Are you here

1123
01:19:59,674 --> 01:20:02,427
to state the obvious?

1124
01:20:02,511 --> 01:20:05,972
"I know you confessed your feelings to me, but you're from a rich family."

1125
01:20:06,056 --> 01:20:07,682
"Our families are too different,

1126
01:20:07,766 --> 01:20:08,975
so it won't work out--"

1127
01:20:09,059 --> 01:20:09,893
Beom-ja.

1128
01:20:09,976 --> 01:20:10,977
Let me talk first.

1129
01:20:11,061 --> 01:20:12,687
Okay. Go on.

1130
01:20:16,233 --> 01:20:17,901
You've been married

1131
01:20:17,984 --> 01:20:18,860
three times--

1132
01:20:18,944 --> 01:20:20,111
I see.

1133
01:20:20,195 --> 01:20:21,655
So that's what this is about.

1134
01:20:22,239 --> 01:20:26,159
You're reluctant to date a woman who was married three times.

1135
01:20:28,203 --> 01:20:30,372
-I understand. -That's not it.

1136
01:20:30,455 --> 01:20:32,707
You've already experienced everything.

1137
01:20:32,791 --> 01:20:34,626
You fell for others, dated them,

1138
01:20:34,709 --> 01:20:36,753
got married, and everything.

1139
01:20:36,837 --> 01:20:39,714
But this is a first for me.

1140
01:20:41,174 --> 01:20:42,968
-What? -I've never dated anyone properly

1141
01:20:43,051 --> 01:20:44,636
even to this day.

1142
01:20:46,847 --> 01:20:48,306
-Seriously? -Yes.

1143
01:20:49,432 --> 01:20:53,854
So it's difficult to walk at your pace.

1144
01:21:19,713 --> 01:21:20,672
It was my first time…

1145
01:21:20,755 --> 01:21:21,882
WAITING MEANS LOVE

1146
01:21:21,965 --> 01:21:23,341
…waiting for someone.

1147
01:21:23,967 --> 01:21:26,136
I've never missed a woman before.

1148
01:21:27,220 --> 01:21:28,930
But then, I got stuck.

1149
01:21:29,014 --> 01:21:32,142
Just like how I got lost today, I don't know which way to go.

1150
01:21:36,062 --> 01:21:37,063
Then…

1151
01:21:38,231 --> 01:21:41,443
what would you like me to do?

1152
01:21:46,072 --> 01:21:49,159
I'm good at cooking and baking.

1153
01:21:49,242 --> 01:21:51,661
I'd like to cook meat for you when you're struggling

1154
01:21:51,745 --> 01:21:54,080
and bake madeleines for you when you're bored.

1155
01:21:54,706 --> 01:21:56,166
I'd like to do that.

1156
01:21:56,249 --> 01:21:59,502
Why don't you visit me when you're struggling

1157
01:22:00,545 --> 01:22:01,588
or feeling bored?

1158
01:22:04,215 --> 01:22:06,217
Okay, I'll do that.

1159
01:22:06,301 --> 01:22:08,845
I'll just come to you if you can't find your way.

1160
01:22:11,640 --> 01:22:14,851
You can take your sweet time.

1161
01:22:22,984 --> 01:22:24,903
Is getting a divorce a trend nowadays?

1162
01:22:24,986 --> 01:22:27,072
Why do you want a divorce?

1163
01:22:27,155 --> 01:22:31,326
If it's not about money, women, or violence,

1164
01:22:31,409 --> 01:22:33,244
then just put up with it.

1165
01:22:33,328 --> 01:22:34,287
It's all of them.

1166
01:22:34,371 --> 01:22:35,413
-All of them? -All of them?

1167
01:22:35,497 --> 01:22:36,414
Chun-sik met

1168
01:22:37,082 --> 01:22:38,917
his first love at a reunion.

1169
01:22:39,000 --> 01:22:40,585
Goodness. Hey.

1170
01:22:40,669 --> 01:22:43,922
There are always first loves at reunions.

1171
01:22:44,005 --> 01:22:46,424
It's normal.

1172
01:22:47,175 --> 01:22:51,888
She works in insurance, and he took out three life insurance policies.

1173
01:22:53,431 --> 01:22:54,474
Unbelievable.

1174
01:22:54,557 --> 01:22:56,601
-And he got violent? -No, that was me.

1175
01:22:56,685 --> 01:23:00,105
I hit him out of rage, and he's demanding a divorce

1176
01:23:00,188 --> 01:23:01,189
because of it.

1177
01:23:01,272 --> 01:23:03,441
So? When will you divorce him?

1178
01:23:03,525 --> 01:23:05,443
I'd love to do it right away.

1179
01:23:07,362 --> 01:23:09,447
But our kid's midterms are coming soon.

1180
01:23:09,531 --> 01:23:10,573
This is a critical moment.

1181
01:23:11,449 --> 01:23:14,077
I thought of divorcing him during the break.

1182
01:23:14,703 --> 01:23:17,831
But we already booked a trip,

1183
01:23:17,914 --> 01:23:18,957
so I can't do that.

1184
01:23:19,499 --> 01:23:21,918
And once school starts, the midterms will come again.

1185
01:23:22,002 --> 01:23:23,753
-Gosh, you're right. -Right.

1186
01:23:25,046 --> 01:23:27,757
Then you'll never divorce him. Just do it now.

1187
01:23:28,800 --> 01:23:29,968
I'll join you.

1188
01:23:31,136 --> 01:23:32,095
Join me?

1189
01:23:32,178 --> 01:23:35,515
We'll suffer less damage if we drop this bomb together.

1190
01:23:35,598 --> 01:23:38,435
Let's time our announcements. I'll go first.

1191
01:23:38,518 --> 01:23:39,936
You can wait a couple days.

1192
01:23:40,020 --> 01:23:42,272
Hey, are you serious?

1193
01:23:46,609 --> 01:23:47,736
Gosh.

1194
01:23:47,819 --> 01:23:49,696
I thought long and hard.

1195
01:23:49,779 --> 01:23:51,698
-It has to be done. -What did that woman say?

1196
01:23:51,781 --> 01:23:53,908
I don't know. Her name is Jenny.

1197
01:23:54,868 --> 01:23:57,120
She said she was his wife or something.

1198
01:23:57,203 --> 01:23:59,330
That's what she said? That she was his wife?

1199
01:23:59,414 --> 01:24:01,958
Yes, that was the context.

1200
01:24:03,668 --> 01:24:06,254
Your husband asked me to relay this message to you.

1201
01:24:06,337 --> 01:24:07,380
Jenny

1202
01:24:07,464 --> 01:24:08,923
-is 60 years old. -What?

1203
01:24:09,007 --> 01:24:10,800
She's the same age as me.

1204
01:24:11,885 --> 01:24:13,470
So he likes older women?

1205
01:24:13,553 --> 01:24:15,221
That's not it.

1206
01:24:15,305 --> 01:24:18,016
He left his phone at the laboratory,

1207
01:24:18,099 --> 01:24:20,310
and his professor picked it up.

1208
01:24:21,186 --> 01:24:22,562
Seriously?

1209
01:24:23,063 --> 01:24:24,606
So she's his professor?

1210
01:24:24,689 --> 01:24:27,442
He was frustrated that he couldn't reach you

1211
01:24:27,525 --> 01:24:29,235
-and asked me to relay this. -Relay what?

1212
01:24:29,319 --> 01:24:30,528
"I love you!"

1213
01:24:32,989 --> 01:24:34,616
Why would he say it to you

1214
01:24:34,699 --> 01:24:36,910
when he could've said it to me?

1215
01:24:37,994 --> 01:24:40,413
He's never said those words to me before.

1216
01:24:40,497 --> 01:24:42,082
You should unblock his number.

1217
01:24:42,165 --> 01:24:43,833
Do you know why wars happen?

1218
01:24:43,917 --> 01:24:46,503
It's due to poor communication.

1219
01:24:46,586 --> 01:24:48,671
Why won't you talk it out?

1220
01:24:48,755 --> 01:24:50,006
Jeez.

1221
01:24:50,673 --> 01:24:51,508
Here.

1222
01:24:54,594 --> 01:24:56,054
What is this?

1223
01:24:56,137 --> 01:24:57,806
A gift from us, the building owners.

1224
01:24:57,889 --> 01:24:59,599
Go see him.

1225
01:24:59,682 --> 01:25:02,894
Look him in the eye and tell him this.

1226
01:25:02,977 --> 01:25:04,145
"I love you"?

1227
01:25:05,063 --> 01:25:06,272
"Me too!"

1228
01:25:09,484 --> 01:25:10,610
Mom…

1229
01:25:12,320 --> 01:25:13,530
Dad…

1230
01:25:17,534 --> 01:25:19,077
Go away.

1231
01:25:19,994 --> 01:25:22,497
Go. Go to the U.S.

1232
01:25:23,998 --> 01:25:25,917
QUEENS DEPARTMENT STORE

1233
01:25:26,668 --> 01:25:27,710
Secretary Na.

1234
01:25:27,794 --> 01:25:29,963
I just got an idea.

1235
01:25:30,046 --> 01:25:31,673
I'm thinking of removing

1236
01:25:31,756 --> 01:25:34,801
these pop-up stores and renovating the area.

1237
01:25:34,884 --> 01:25:38,304
-I'd like to have a plaza-- -So that kids can run around?

1238
01:25:39,097 --> 01:25:41,724
Yes, and I want resting spaces--

1239
01:25:41,808 --> 01:25:44,144
We're going to make plenty of them.

1240
01:25:45,061 --> 01:25:47,438
You already told me this before the surgery.

1241
01:25:47,522 --> 01:25:48,398
I did?

1242
01:25:48,481 --> 01:25:51,693
I guess some things never change despite losing your memory.

1243
01:26:02,328 --> 01:26:03,288
Did you have lunch?

1244
01:26:03,371 --> 01:26:04,664
I was about to.

1245
01:26:05,832 --> 01:26:06,958
Enjoy.

1246
01:26:07,792 --> 01:26:08,668
Enjoy your lunch.

1247
01:26:18,052 --> 01:26:19,470
When will you get married?

1248
01:26:20,972 --> 01:26:22,724
-Don't be absurd. -Are you not?

1249
01:26:23,808 --> 01:26:24,642
No.

1250
01:26:24,726 --> 01:26:25,935
Think about it.

1251
01:26:26,019 --> 01:26:29,939
He's like a stranger I'm just getting to know.

1252
01:26:30,023 --> 01:26:32,025
I like him, and I'm grateful.

1253
01:26:32,108 --> 01:26:34,611
But our love temperatures differ.

1254
01:26:34,694 --> 01:26:35,653
Do they?

1255
01:26:36,529 --> 01:26:39,490
Of course. His temperature is about 180°C.

1256
01:26:40,825 --> 01:26:43,161
It's hot enough to fry this chicken.

1257
01:26:43,244 --> 01:26:45,705
Unlike him who's boiling hot,

1258
01:26:45,788 --> 01:26:49,167
my temperature is just enough for a cup of coffee.

1259
01:26:49,834 --> 01:26:53,546
That's why it's too soon to talk about marriage.

1260
01:26:55,381 --> 01:26:56,216
Why do you ask?

1261
01:26:57,008 --> 01:26:58,176
Is that what he said?

1262
01:26:58,259 --> 01:26:59,761
-Does he want to marry me? -No.

1263
01:27:02,096 --> 01:27:03,306
-No? -No.

1264
01:27:03,389 --> 01:27:04,974
He never said such a thing.

1265
01:27:05,058 --> 01:27:06,935
It was just something everyone assumed.

1266
01:27:07,018 --> 01:27:08,937
He still proposed, didn't he?

1267
01:27:12,440 --> 01:27:15,109
I don't remember it, but he did in the past.

1268
01:27:15,735 --> 01:27:17,403
-I even have the ring at home. -Come on.

1269
01:27:17,487 --> 01:27:19,405
You don't even remember that,

1270
01:27:19,489 --> 01:27:20,490
so it doesn't count.

1271
01:27:20,573 --> 01:27:21,699
Did he not propose again?

1272
01:27:22,742 --> 01:27:24,994
Seriously? That's cold.

1273
01:27:27,538 --> 01:27:28,373
NEW MESSAGE

1274
01:27:32,877 --> 01:27:34,963
Ma'am, the time has come.

1275
01:27:35,046 --> 01:27:36,464
What do you mean?

1276
01:27:36,547 --> 01:27:38,925
Director Baek made a reservation at a restaurant

1277
01:27:39,008 --> 01:27:41,261
where many people propose.

1278
01:27:42,720 --> 01:27:43,763
Unbelievable.

1279
01:27:44,347 --> 01:27:45,932
I'm not ready yet.

1280
01:27:46,557 --> 01:27:48,226
Why is he getting ahead of himself?

1281
01:27:48,309 --> 01:27:49,477
How can I reject him?

1282
01:27:50,186 --> 01:27:53,147
I don't want to hurt someone who took a bullet for me.

1283
01:28:34,647 --> 01:28:35,523
Come on.

1284
01:28:35,606 --> 01:28:37,400
He should call me

1285
01:28:38,067 --> 01:28:39,444
if he booked a restaurant.

1286
01:28:41,821 --> 01:28:42,905
I'm hungry.

1287
01:28:45,116 --> 01:28:46,743
Jeez.

1288
01:28:46,826 --> 01:28:47,785
BAEK HYUN-WOO

1289
01:28:50,872 --> 01:28:52,999
Hello?

1290
01:28:54,876 --> 01:28:56,210
I mean…

1291
01:28:56,294 --> 01:28:57,295
Where are you

1292
01:28:58,755 --> 01:28:59,589
right now?

1293
01:28:59,672 --> 01:29:00,882
-Cheers! -Cheers!

1294
01:29:00,965 --> 01:29:04,052
I'm having a company dinner at a restaurant.

1295
01:29:05,720 --> 01:29:07,764
Is something going on? Are you unwell?

1296
01:29:08,723 --> 01:29:10,058
No, I'm not.

1297
01:29:10,558 --> 01:29:14,187
I'm fine. Enjoy your dinner.

1298
01:29:19,192 --> 01:29:20,360
A company dinner?

1299
01:29:57,480 --> 01:29:58,481
What's that?

1300
01:29:59,399 --> 01:30:00,650
He's not a kid anymore.

1301
01:30:00,733 --> 01:30:01,734
Get rid of them.

1302
01:30:05,738 --> 01:30:07,615
Remove…

1303
01:30:07,698 --> 01:30:10,535
all those glow-in-the-dark stars and all the objects.

1304
01:30:30,388 --> 01:30:32,348
How could you move your stuff without telling me?

1305
01:30:32,432 --> 01:30:34,684
You never told me you were emptying this room either.

1306
01:30:34,767 --> 01:30:36,185
What are you getting at?

1307
01:30:38,062 --> 01:30:39,939
Are you blaming me for the miscarriage?

1308
01:30:40,022 --> 01:30:41,274
What are you saying?

1309
01:30:41,357 --> 01:30:44,110
I never thought that way. I'm just as sad as you--

1310
01:30:44,193 --> 01:30:45,486
Don't lie.

1311
01:30:46,112 --> 01:30:48,948
I know you want to say that it's my fault!

1312
01:30:54,203 --> 01:30:55,329
Forget it.

1313
01:30:55,413 --> 01:30:57,331
I can't talk any sense into you.

1314
01:31:34,076 --> 01:31:35,953
I waited for you yesterday.

1315
01:31:36,579 --> 01:31:39,248
I heard you booked a restaurant

1316
01:31:39,332 --> 01:31:41,250
where many people proposed at.

1317
01:31:41,334 --> 01:31:42,960
I was shocked because I thought

1318
01:31:43,044 --> 01:31:45,171
you wanted to propose to me again.

1319
01:31:45,254 --> 01:31:48,174
I thought long and hard about how to let you down gently.

1320
01:31:50,092 --> 01:31:53,095
So you were planning to reject me

1321
01:31:53,179 --> 01:31:54,847
if I proposed?

1322
01:31:54,931 --> 01:31:56,265
Yes.

1323
01:31:57,099 --> 01:31:58,017
But you never did,

1324
01:31:59,894 --> 01:32:01,020
so I couldn't reject you.

1325
01:32:02,813 --> 01:32:04,190
I'm sorry.

1326
01:32:05,233 --> 01:32:06,317
But why?

1327
01:32:07,318 --> 01:32:08,778
Why would you reject me?

1328
01:32:08,861 --> 01:32:10,071
Because I'm scared.

1329
01:32:10,863 --> 01:32:13,783
We're on good terms. I don't want to ruin that.

1330
01:32:21,082 --> 01:32:21,958
But it's too late.

1331
01:32:23,125 --> 01:32:25,878
I would've rejected you had you proposed yesterday,

1332
01:32:26,504 --> 01:32:28,130
but I've changed my mind now.

1333
01:32:30,675 --> 01:32:33,511
I remembered my worst memory last night.

1334
01:32:36,013 --> 01:32:38,182
It devastated and hurt me greatly.

1335
01:32:39,100 --> 01:32:40,601
But I was relieved as well.

1336
01:32:41,769 --> 01:32:44,897
I'm less afraid now than when I was in the dark.

1337
01:32:47,817 --> 01:32:49,527
We probably fell apart

1338
01:32:50,111 --> 01:32:52,989
due to trivial matters.

1339
01:32:53,072 --> 01:32:55,408
We said things we didn't mean

1340
01:32:55,908 --> 01:32:57,451
and protected our ego.

1341
01:32:57,535 --> 01:32:59,704
And that caused stupid misunderstandings.

1342
01:33:00,371 --> 01:33:02,582
Instead of knocking on your door,

1343
01:33:03,249 --> 01:33:04,208
it was probably easier

1344
01:33:04,792 --> 01:33:07,253
to stay in my room

1345
01:33:08,462 --> 01:33:09,589
and resent you.

1346
01:33:10,715 --> 01:33:11,549
But…

1347
01:33:13,092 --> 01:33:14,552
I won't do that anymore.

1348
01:33:16,804 --> 01:33:18,723
Then maybe we can give it a try.

1349
01:33:25,605 --> 01:33:26,731
Me too.

1350
01:33:27,440 --> 01:33:28,524
I felt the same way.

1351
01:33:30,401 --> 01:33:32,737
I'll never be afraid

1352
01:33:33,613 --> 01:33:36,032
to take another bullet for you.

1353
01:33:36,115 --> 01:33:38,784
But I was afraid

1354
01:33:39,285 --> 01:33:40,286
we'd become exhausted

1355
01:33:41,537 --> 01:33:47,001
and disappointed in each other after arguing over…

1356
01:33:49,712 --> 01:33:50,713
the most trivial things.

1357
01:33:51,380 --> 01:33:53,591
I wasn't confident that we wouldn't fall apart

1358
01:33:53,674 --> 01:33:55,593
or resent each other…

1359
01:33:58,429 --> 01:33:59,597
once again.

1360
01:34:01,641 --> 01:34:03,392
But I can promise you this.

1361
01:34:19,617 --> 01:34:20,826
I'll stay by your side.

1362
01:34:23,746 --> 01:34:25,498
No matter what happens,

1363
01:34:30,419 --> 01:34:32,254
I can mend things

1364
01:34:32,338 --> 01:34:34,006
when they're broken.

1365
01:34:34,924 --> 01:34:38,010
It may not always be perfect.

1366
01:34:41,764 --> 01:34:42,598
But I can do that.

1367
01:34:44,934 --> 01:34:46,227
If that's okay with you,

1368
01:34:46,727 --> 01:34:48,062
then will you marry me?

1369
01:34:53,526 --> 01:34:54,360
Of course.

1370
01:34:58,823 --> 01:34:59,990
But…

1371
01:35:01,075 --> 01:35:02,284
I do need more time.

1372
01:35:04,495 --> 01:35:06,122
We're still in the beginning stages.

1373
01:35:09,375 --> 01:35:11,335
So please don't rush.

1374
01:35:14,046 --> 01:35:15,214
Right.

1375
01:35:15,715 --> 01:35:16,632
Okay.

1376
01:35:16,716 --> 01:35:17,717
You can only hug me

1377
01:35:18,634 --> 01:35:21,470
after we hold hands at least five times.

1378
01:35:22,012 --> 01:35:22,847
What…

1379
01:35:24,348 --> 01:35:25,224
Five times?

1380
01:35:34,775 --> 01:35:37,445
I'd like to have breakfast together every morning.

1381
01:35:39,739 --> 01:35:41,782
It's healthy to have breakfast,

1382
01:35:41,866 --> 01:35:43,033
so that's fine.

1383
01:35:44,452 --> 01:35:45,619
And taking walks every day?

1384
01:35:45,703 --> 01:35:48,372
Vitamin D is crucial,

1385
01:35:48,456 --> 01:35:49,790
so that's a good idea too.

1386
01:35:49,874 --> 01:35:52,126
What about going on a trip every season?

1387
01:35:52,877 --> 01:35:56,172
Getting good rest will help us work better.

1388
01:35:57,548 --> 01:35:58,758
That's a good plan.

1389
01:36:02,720 --> 01:36:05,222
We'll have to be

1390
01:36:05,306 --> 01:36:06,807
-on our toes. -Why?

1391
01:36:07,558 --> 01:36:09,226
Because life never unfolds

1392
01:36:09,310 --> 01:36:11,103
the way you want it to.

1393
01:36:11,187 --> 01:36:13,689
CORRECTIONAL WELFARE THAT LEADS TO A BRIGHTER FUTURE

1394
01:36:27,745 --> 01:36:29,622
Geon-u, why don't you go to your mom?

1395
01:36:36,712 --> 01:36:39,423
Geon-u, do you know who I am?

1396
01:36:39,507 --> 01:36:41,008
-Do you remember me? -Yes.

1397
01:36:43,385 --> 01:36:44,470
I'm sorry.

1398
01:36:44,970 --> 01:36:47,640
I'm sorry. I love you.

1399
01:36:47,723 --> 01:36:49,892
-Mom. -I'm sorry, Geon-u.

1400
01:36:50,893 --> 01:36:52,228
Geon-u can ride

1401
01:36:52,311 --> 01:36:54,188
a tricycle now, honey.

1402
01:36:55,147 --> 01:36:55,981
I taught him.

1403
01:36:58,859 --> 01:36:59,944
Let me show you.

1404
01:37:10,329 --> 01:37:11,205
Well done.

1405
01:37:12,498 --> 01:37:13,541
Come to the cafe.

1406
01:37:13,624 --> 01:37:15,334
I'll give you freebies.

1407
01:37:15,417 --> 01:37:16,710
Bye.

1408
01:37:18,921 --> 01:37:20,005
Geon-u.

1409
01:37:21,173 --> 01:37:22,174
Is it really spring?

1410
01:37:22,967 --> 01:37:24,426
Why does it feel colder…

1411
01:37:24,510 --> 01:37:27,012
-What should we do? -…out here?

1412
01:37:33,978 --> 01:37:35,020
Where are you going?

1413
01:37:37,189 --> 01:37:39,859
My mom told me to pick you up. We're going to eat together.

1414
01:37:42,778 --> 01:37:43,612
Me too?

1415
01:37:45,072 --> 01:37:47,324
-Really? -Hurry up.

1416
01:37:47,408 --> 01:37:50,911
Ms. Kim is the best.

1417
01:37:50,995 --> 01:37:53,622
-Geon-u, you grew up so much. -She's my friend.

1418
01:37:55,583 --> 01:37:56,542
Let's get a move on.

1419
01:37:56,625 --> 01:38:00,170
-Let's go! -We forgave those we used to resent.

1420
01:38:14,351 --> 01:38:16,854
Look, Mr. Kim.

1421
01:38:17,479 --> 01:38:19,690
Do you know the proportional theory?

1422
01:38:19,773 --> 01:38:21,650
-It's when-- -Yes, I do.

1423
01:38:21,734 --> 01:38:23,485
Time accelerates

1424
01:38:23,569 --> 01:38:25,404
when there's little time.

1425
01:38:25,487 --> 01:38:28,032
I'm aging quickly as well.

1426
01:38:28,616 --> 01:38:30,618
My wrists ached yesterday.

1427
01:38:30,701 --> 01:38:32,328
Today, my knees cracked.

1428
01:38:32,411 --> 01:38:33,579
You should take omega-3--

1429
01:38:35,164 --> 01:38:36,749
That's not why.

1430
01:38:36,832 --> 01:38:38,667
How long will you drag this on?

1431
01:38:38,751 --> 01:38:40,920
I didn't know you'd take this much time.

1432
01:38:48,677 --> 01:38:51,096
We'll have our first kiss by the time I'm all wrinkly!

1433
01:39:48,195 --> 01:39:51,115
We realized that some things won't happen even if we try hard.

1434
01:39:51,198 --> 01:39:54,034
But even if that's the case,

1435
01:39:54,118 --> 01:39:56,078
we learned that it's okay.

1436
01:39:56,620 --> 01:39:57,830
QUEEN'S BOXING GYM

1437
01:39:57,913 --> 01:40:00,749
Muhammad Ali once said this.

1438
01:40:00,833 --> 01:40:05,129
"Live every day as if it were your last."

1439
01:40:05,212 --> 01:40:08,590
"Then you'll find the answer one day."

1440
01:40:08,674 --> 01:40:11,218
So you should live every day--

1441
01:40:11,301 --> 01:40:12,553
Hold on. I'm getting a call.

1442
01:40:12,636 --> 01:40:13,762
Keep going.

1443
01:40:13,846 --> 01:40:15,014
Keep your guard up.

1444
01:40:16,390 --> 01:40:17,307
Hi, Mom.

1445
01:40:17,391 --> 01:40:19,935
Don't be a terrible landlord.

1446
01:40:20,019 --> 01:40:21,353
Gosh.

1447
01:40:22,688 --> 01:40:23,981
I miss Hae-in.

1448
01:40:24,815 --> 01:40:27,568
She was a landlord who didn't even know she owned this place.

1449
01:40:27,651 --> 01:40:30,070
We live every day to the fullest.

1450
01:40:36,326 --> 01:40:37,286
Gosh.

1451
01:40:39,079 --> 01:40:41,874
I can't believe you let your brother become the chairman

1452
01:40:41,957 --> 01:40:44,626
and chose to have ramyeon here instead.

1453
01:40:45,127 --> 01:40:46,336
I like it.

1454
01:40:46,420 --> 01:40:48,505
This is where I belong.

1455
01:40:48,589 --> 01:40:54,136
I can finally say goodbye to others without thinking about betraying them.

1456
01:40:55,262 --> 01:40:57,848
This is paradise for me!

1457
01:40:58,849 --> 01:41:03,270
What kind of paradise doesn't have kimchi? Ramyeon and kimchi go hand in hand.

1458
01:41:07,649 --> 01:41:09,568
-Is it working? -Yes, it is.

1459
01:41:09,651 --> 01:41:12,237
Gosh. We looked everywhere for you.

1460
01:41:12,321 --> 01:41:13,947
We brought some kimchi.

1461
01:41:14,031 --> 01:41:16,158
The ramyeon is ready too!

1462
01:41:16,241 --> 01:41:17,576
-Good. -Come on over.

1463
01:41:18,911 --> 01:41:22,081
-Goodness. Hold on. -Hello.

1464
01:41:22,164 --> 01:41:24,666
-Hello. -Don't greet her right now.

1465
01:41:24,750 --> 01:41:26,043
How do I stop this?

1466
01:41:26,126 --> 01:41:27,252
-The brakes! -What?

1467
01:41:27,336 --> 01:41:28,879
The brakes! Step on the brakes!

1468
01:41:28,962 --> 01:41:30,672
-Not the gear stick! -Where are you going?

1469
01:41:30,756 --> 01:41:31,924
Du-gwan, over here!

1470
01:41:32,007 --> 01:41:33,175
We can sometimes stop

1471
01:41:33,258 --> 01:41:35,177
and appreciate the scenery.

1472
01:41:38,847 --> 01:41:41,642
Then time will gradually begin to flow more quickly.

1473
01:41:47,856 --> 01:41:49,399
Time will slip away,

1474
01:41:49,483 --> 01:41:51,568
and we won't be able to do anything about it.

1475
01:42:03,914 --> 01:42:05,457
That's how we'll spend

1476
01:42:06,583 --> 01:42:07,918
every day of our lives.

1477
01:42:21,557 --> 01:42:25,018
We'll enjoy all the happiness that life grants us.

1478
01:43:55,025 --> 01:43:58,528
HONG HAE-IN 22 AUGUST 1990, 7 APRIL 2074

1479
01:43:58,612 --> 01:44:02,324
SPENDING MY LIFE WITH YOU HAS BEEN A MIRACLE

1480
01:44:45,951 --> 01:44:46,952
One day…

1481
01:44:49,079 --> 01:44:51,081
when only one of us is left…

1482
01:45:24,281 --> 01:45:27,534
The other one can come meet them.

1483
01:45:35,459 --> 01:45:37,377
Then it won't be scary at all.

1484
01:45:42,174 --> 01:45:44,426
-Because we'll be together. -Because we'll be together.

1485
01:49:18,181 --> 01:49:20,183
Subtitle translation by: Soo-ji Kim
